  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The History of Creation'
      title: The History of Creation
      number: 1
      content: 'In the beginning God created the heavens and the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: The earth was without form, and void; and darkness was on the face
        of the deep. And the Spirit of God was hovering over the face of the waters.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then God said, \u201CLet there be light\u201D; and there was light. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And God saw the light, that it  was good; and God divided the light
        from the darkness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: God called the light Day, and the darkness He called Night. So the
        evening and the morning were the first day.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then God said, \u201CLet there be a firmament in the midst of the
        waters, and let it divide the waters from the waters.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Thus God made the firmament, and divided the waters which were under
        the firmament from the waters which were  above the firmament; and it was
        so. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: And God called the firmament Heaven. So the evening and the morning
        were the second day.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then God said, \u201CLet the waters under the heavens be gathered
        together into one place, and let the dry land appear\u201D; and it was so. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: And God called the dry land Earth, and the gathering together of the
        waters He called Seas. And God saw that it  was good.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then God said, \u201CLet the earth bring forth grass, the herb that
        yields seed, and the fruit tree that yields fruit according to its kind,
        whose seed is in itself, on the earth\u201D; and it was so. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And the earth brought forth grass, the herb that yields seed according
        to its kind, and the tree that yields fruit, whose seed is in itself according
        to its kind. And God saw that it  was good. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: So the evening and the morning were the third day.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then God said, \u201CLet there be lights in the firmament of the
        heavens to divide the day from the night; and let them be for signs and seasons,
        and for days and years; "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "and let them be for lights in the firmament of the heavens to give
        light on the earth\u201D; and it was so. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Then God made two great lights: the greater light to rule the day,
        and the lesser light to rule the night. He  made  the stars also. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'God set them in the firmament of the heavens to give light on the
        earth, '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'and to rule over the day and over the night, and to divide the light
        from the darkness. And God saw that it  was good. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: So the evening and the morning were the fourth day.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Then God said, \u201CLet the waters abound with an abundance of living
        creatures, and let birds fly above the earth across the face of the firmament
        of the heavens.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'So God created great sea creatures and every living thing that moves,
        with which the waters abounded, according to their kind, and every winged
        bird according to its kind. And God saw that it  was good. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "And God blessed them, saying, \u201CBe fruitful and multiply, and
        fill the waters in the seas, and let birds multiply on the earth.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: So the evening and the morning were the fifth day.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Then God said, \u201CLet the earth bring forth the living creature
        according to its kind: cattle and creeping thing and beast of the earth,
        each according to its kind\u201D; and it was so. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: And God made the beast of the earth according to its kind, cattle
        according to its kind, and everything that creeps on the earth according
        to its kind. And God saw that it  was good.
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Then God said, \u201CLet Us make man in Our image, according to Our
        likeness; let them have dominion over the fish of the sea, over the birds
        of the air, and over the cattle, over all the earth and over every creeping
        thing that creeps on the earth.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'So God created man in His own image; in the image of God He created
        him; male and female He created them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Then God blessed them, and God said to them, \u201CBe fruitful and
        multiply; fill the earth and subdue it; have dominion over the fish of the
        sea, over the birds of the air, and over every living thing that moves on
        the earth.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "And God said, \u201CSee, I have given you every herb that yields
        seed which is on the face of all the earth, and every tree whose fruit yields
        seed; to you it shall be for food. "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Also, to every beast of the earth, to every bird of the air, and
        to everything that creeps on the earth, in which there  is life, I  have 
        given every green herb for food\u201D; and it was so. "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: Then God saw everything that He had made, and indeed it  was very
        good. So the evening and the morning were the sixth day.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: 'Thus the heavens and the earth, and all the host of them, were finished. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And on the seventh day God ended His work which He had done, and
        He rested on the seventh day from all His work which He had done. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: Then God blessed the seventh day and sanctified it, because in it
        He rested from all His work which God had created and made.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'This is the history of the heavens and the earth when they were created,
        in the day that the Lord God made the earth and the heavens, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'before any plant of the field was in the earth and before any herb
        of the field had grown. For the Lord God had not caused it to rain on the
        earth, and there  was no man to till the ground; '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: but a mist went up from the earth and watered the whole face of the
        ground.
      comments: []
    - name: "7: Life in God\u2019s Garden"
      title: "Life in God\u2019s Garden"
      number: 7
      content: And the Lord God formed man of the dust of the ground, and breathed
        into his nostrils the breath of life; and man became a living being.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The Lord God planted a garden eastward in Eden, and there He put
        the man whom He had formed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: And out of the ground the Lord God made every tree grow that is pleasant
        to the sight and good for food. The tree of life was also in the midst of
        the garden, and the tree of the knowledge of good and evil.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Now a river went out of Eden to water the garden, and from there
        it parted and became four riverheads. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'The name of the first is Pishon; it is the one which skirts the whole
        land of Havilah, where there  is gold. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And the gold of that land is good. Bdellium and the onyx stone are
        there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'The name of the second river is Gihon; it is the one which goes around
        the whole land of Cush. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: The name of the third river is  Hiddekel; it is the one which goes
        toward the east of Assyria. The fourth river is the Euphrates.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Then the Lord God took the man and put him in the garden of Eden
        to tend and keep it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And the Lord God commanded the man, saying, \u201COf every tree of
        the garden you may freely eat; "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "but of the tree of the knowledge of good and evil you shall not eat,
        for in the day that you eat of it you shall surely die.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And the Lord God said, \u201CIt  is not good that man should be alone;
        I will make him a helper comparable to him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Out of the ground the Lord God formed every beast of the field and
        every bird of the air, and brought them to Adam to see what he would call
        them. And whatever Adam called each living creature, that was its name. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: So Adam gave names to all cattle, to the birds of the air, and to
        every beast of the field. But for Adam there was not found a helper comparable
        to him.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And the Lord God caused a deep sleep to fall on Adam, and he slept;
        and He took one of his ribs, and closed up the flesh in its place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: Then the rib which the Lord God had taken from man He made into a
        woman, and He brought her to the man.
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "And Adam said:\u201CThis is now bone of my bonesAnd flesh of my flesh;She
        shall be called Woman,Because she was taken out of Man.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: Therefore a man shall leave his father and mother and be joined to
        his wife, and they shall become one flesh.
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: And they were both naked, the man and his wife, and were not ashamed.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Temptation and Fall of Man'
      title: The Temptation and Fall of Man
      number: 1
      content: "Now the serpent was more cunning than any beast of the field which
        the Lord God had made. And he said to the woman, \u201CHas God indeed said,
        \u2018You shall not eat of every tree of the garden\u2019?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And the woman said to the serpent, \u201CWe may eat the fruit of
        the trees of the garden; "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "but of the fruit of the tree which is in the midst of the garden,
        God has said, \u2018You shall not eat it, nor shall you touch it, lest you
        die.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Then the serpent said to the woman, \u201CYou will not surely die. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "For God knows that in the day you eat of it your eyes will be opened,
        and you will be like God, knowing good and evil.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'So when the woman saw that the tree was good for food, that it was
        pleasant to the eyes, and a tree desirable to make one wise, she took of
        its fruit and ate. She also gave to her husband with her, and he ate. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: Then the eyes of both of them were opened, and they knew that they
        were naked; and they sewed fig leaves together and made themselves coverings.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: And they heard the sound of the Lord God walking in the garden in
        the cool of the day, and Adam and his wife hid themselves from the presence
        of the Lord God among the trees of the garden.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then the Lord God called to Adam and said to him, \u201CWhere are
        you?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "So he said, \u201CI heard Your voice in the garden, and I was afraid
        because I was naked; and I hid myself.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And He said, \u201CWho told you that you were naked? Have you eaten
        from the tree of which I commanded you that you should not eat?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then the man said, \u201CThe woman whom You gave to  be with me,
        she gave me of the tree, and I ate.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And the Lord God said to the woman, \u201CWhat is this you have done?\u201DThe
        woman said, \u201CThe serpent deceived me, and I ate.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "So the Lord God said to the serpent:\u201CBecause you have done this,You
        are cursed more than all cattle,And more than every beast of the field;On
        your belly you shall go,And you shall eat dustAll the days of your life."
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And I will put enmityBetween you and the woman,And between your seed
        and her Seed;He shall bruise your head,And you shall bruise His heel.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "To the woman He said:\u201CI will greatly multiply your sorrow and
        your conception;In pain you shall bring forth children;Your desire shall 
        be for your husband,And he shall rule over you.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Then to Adam He said, \u201CBecause you have heeded the voice of
        your wife, and have eaten from the tree of which I commanded you, saying,
        \u2018You shall not eat of it\u2019:\u201CCursed is the ground for your sake;In
        toil you shall eat of itAll the days of your life."
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: Both thorns and thistles it shall bring forth for you,And you shall
        eat the herb of the field.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "In the sweat of your face you shall eat breadTill you return to the
        ground,For out of it you were taken;For dust you are,And to dust you shall
        return.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And Adam called his wife\u2019s name Eve, because she was the mother
        of all living."
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: Also for Adam and his wife the Lord God made tunics of skin, and clothed
        them.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Then the Lord God said, \u201CBehold, the man has become like one
        of Us, to know good and evil. And now, lest he put out his hand and take
        also of the tree of life, and eat, and live forever\u201D\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'therefore the Lord God sent him out of the garden of Eden to till
        the ground from which he was taken. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: So He drove out the man; and He placed cherubim at the east of the
        garden of Eden, and a flaming sword which turned every way, to guard the
        way to the tree of life.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Cain Murders Abel'
      title: Cain Murders Abel
      number: 1
      content: "Now Adam knew Eve his wife, and she conceived and bore Cain, and
        said, \u201CI have acquired a man from the Lord.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Then she bore again, this time his brother Abel. Now Abel was a keeper
        of sheep, but Cain was a tiller of the ground. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And in the process of time it came to pass that Cain brought an offering
        of the fruit of the ground to the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Abel also brought of the firstborn of his flock and of their fat.
        And the Lord respected Abel and his offering, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: but He did not respect Cain and his offering. And Cain was very angry,
        and his countenance fell.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "So the Lord said to Cain, \u201CWhy are you angry? And why has your
        countenance fallen? "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "If you do well, will you not be accepted? And if you do not do well,
        sin lies at the door. And its desire is for you, but you should rule over
        it.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: Now Cain talked with Abel his brother; and it came to pass, when they
        were in the field, that Cain rose up against Abel his brother and killed
        him.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then the Lord said to Cain, \u201CWhere is Abel your brother?\u201DHe
        said, \u201CI do not know. Am I my brother\u2019s keeper?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And He said, \u201CWhat have you done? The voice of your brother\u2019s
        blood cries out to Me from the ground. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "So now you are cursed from the earth, which has opened its mouth
        to receive your brother\u2019s blood from your hand. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "When you till the ground, it shall no longer yield its strength to
        you. A fugitive and a vagabond you shall be on the earth.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And Cain said to the Lord, \u201CMy punishment is greater than I
        can bear! "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Surely You have driven me out this day from the face of the ground;
        I shall be hidden from Your face; I shall be a fugitive and a vagabond on
        the earth, and it will happen that  anyone who finds me will kill me.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '15: The Family of Cain'
      title: The Family of Cain
      number: 15
      content: "And the Lord said to him, \u201CTherefore, whoever kills Cain, vengeance
        shall be taken on him sevenfold.\u201D And the Lord set a mark on Cain, lest
        anyone finding him should kill him."
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Then Cain went out from the presence of the Lord and dwelt in the
        land of Nod on the east of Eden. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And Cain knew his wife, and she conceived and bore \u0112\xB4noch.
        And he built a city, and called the name of the city after the name of his
        son\u2014\u0112\xB4noch. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "To \u0112\xB4noch was born Irad; and Irad begot Mehujael, and Mehujael
        begot Methushael, and Methushael begot Lamech."
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Then Lamech took for himself two wives: the name of one was Adah,
        and the name of the second was Zillah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And Adah bore Jabal. He was the father of those who dwell in tents
        and have livestock. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "His brother\u2019s name was Jubal. He was the father of all those
        who play the harp and flute. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: And as for Zillah, she also bore Tubal-Cain, an instructor of every
        craftsman in bronze and iron. And the sister of Tubal-Cain was Naamah.
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Then Lamech said to his wives:\u201CAdah and Zillah, hear my voice;Wives
        of Lamech, listen to my speech!For I have killed a man for wounding me,Even
        a young man for hurting me."
      comments: []
    - name: '24: A New Son'
      title: A New Son
      number: 24
      content: "If Cain shall be avenged sevenfold,Then Lamech seventy-sevenfold.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "And Adam knew his wife again, and she bore a son and named him Seth,
        \u201CFor God has appointed another seed for me instead of Abel, whom Cain
        killed.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "And as for Seth, to him also a son was born; and he named him \u0112\xB4nosh.
        Then men began to call on the name of the Lord."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Family of Adam'
      title: The Family of Adam
      number: 1
      content: 'This is the book of the genealogy of Adam. In the day that God created
        man, He made him in the likeness of God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'He created them male and female, and blessed them and called them
        Mankind in the day they were created. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And Adam lived one hundred and thirty years, and begot a  son  in
        his own likeness, after his image, and named him Seth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'After he begot Seth, the days of Adam were eight hundred years; and
        he had sons and daughters. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: So all the days that Adam lived were nine hundred and thirty years;
        and he died.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Seth lived one hundred and five years, and begot Enosh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'After he begot Enosh, Seth lived eight hundred and seven years, and
        had sons and daughters. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: So all the days of Seth were nine hundred and twelve years; and he
        died.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Enosh lived ninety years, and begot Cainan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'After he begot Cainan, Enosh lived eight hundred and fifteen years,
        and had sons and daughters. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: So all the days of Enosh were nine hundred and five years; and he
        died.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Cainan lived seventy years, and begot Mahalalel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'After he begot Mahalalel, Cainan lived eight hundred and forty years,
        and had sons and daughters. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: So all the days of Cainan were nine hundred and ten years; and he
        died.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Mahalalel lived sixty-five years, and begot Jared. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'After he begot Jared, Mahalalel lived eight hundred and thirty years,
        and had sons and daughters. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: So all the days of Mahalalel were eight hundred and ninety-five years;
        and he died.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Jared lived one hundred and sixty-two years, and begot Enoch. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'After he begot Enoch, Jared lived eight hundred years, and had sons
        and daughters. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: So all the days of Jared were nine hundred and sixty-two years; and
        he died.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Enoch lived sixty-five years, and begot Methuselah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'After he begot Methuselah, Enoch walked with God three hundred years,
        and had sons and daughters. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'So all the days of Enoch were three hundred and sixty-five years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: And Enoch walked with God; and he was not, for God took him.
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Methuselah lived one hundred and eighty-seven years, and begot Lamech. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'After he begot Lamech, Methuselah lived seven hundred and eighty-two
        years, and had sons and daughters. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: So all the days of Methuselah were nine hundred and sixty-nine years;
        and he died.
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Lamech lived one hundred and eighty-two years, and had a son. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "And he called his name Noah, saying, \u201CThis one will comfort
        us concerning our work and the toil of our hands, because of the ground which
        the Lord has cursed.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'After he begot Noah, Lamech lived five hundred and ninety-five years,
        and had sons and daughters. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: So all the days of Lamech were seven hundred and seventy-seven years;
        and he died.
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: And Noah was five hundred years old, and Noah begot Shem, Ham, and
        Japheth.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Wickedness and Judgment of Man'
      title: The Wickedness and Judgment of Man
      number: 1
      content: 'Now it came to pass, when men began to multiply on the face of the
        earth, and daughters were born to them, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: that the sons of God saw the daughters of men, that they were beautiful;
        and they took wives for themselves of all whom they chose.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And the Lord said, \u201CMy Spirit shall not strive with man forever,
        for he is indeed flesh; yet his days shall be one hundred and twenty years.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: There were giants on the earth in those days, and also afterward,
        when the sons of God came in to the daughters of men and they bore children
        to them. Those were the mighty men who were of old, men of renown.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Then the Lord saw that the wickedness of man was great in the earth,
        and that every intent of the thoughts of his heart was only evil continually. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And the Lord was sorry that He had made man on the earth, and He
        was grieved in His heart. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "So the Lord said, \u201CI will destroy man whom I have created from
        the face of the earth, both man and beast, creeping thing and birds of the
        air, for I am sorry that I have made them.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: Noah Pleases God'
      title: Noah Pleases God
      number: 8
      content: But Noah found grace in the eyes of the Lord.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'This is the genealogy of Noah. Noah was a just man, perfect in his
        generations. Noah walked with God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And Noah begot three sons: Shem, Ham, and Japheth.'
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'The earth also was corrupt before God, and the earth was filled with
        violence. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: The Ark Prepared'
      title: The Ark Prepared
      number: 12
      content: So God looked upon the earth, and indeed it was corrupt; for all flesh
        had corrupted their way on the earth.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And God said to Noah, \u201CThe end of all flesh has come before
        Me, for the earth is filled with violence through them; and behold, I will
        destroy them with the earth. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Make yourself an ark of gopherwood; make rooms in the ark, and cover
        it inside and outside with pitch. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And this is how you shall make it: The length of the ark shall  be
        three hundred cubits, its width fifty cubits, and its height thirty cubits. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'You shall make a window for the ark, and you shall finish it to a
        cubit from above; and set the door of the ark in its side. You shall make
        it with lower, second, and third decks.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And behold, I Myself am bringing floodwaters on the earth, to destroy
        from under heaven all flesh in which is the breath of life; everything that
        is on the earth shall die. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "But I will establish My covenant with you; and you shall go into
        the ark\u2014you, your sons, your wife, and your sons\u2019 wives with you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And of every living thing of all flesh you shall bring two of every
        sort into the ark, to keep them alive with you; they shall be male and female. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Of the birds after their kind, of animals after their kind, and of
        every creeping thing of the earth after its kind, two of every kind  will
        come to you to keep them alive. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "And you shall take for yourself of all food that is eaten, and you
        shall gather it to yourself; and it shall be food for you and for them.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: Thus Noah did; according to all that God commanded him, so he did.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Great Flood'
      title: The Great Flood
      number: 1
      content: "Then the Lord said to Noah, \u201CCome into the ark, you and all
        your household, because I have seen that  you are righteous before Me in
        this generation. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'You shall take with you seven each of every clean animal, a male
        and his female; two each of animals that are unclean, a male and his female; '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'also seven each of birds of the air, male and female, to keep the
        species alive on the face of all the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "For after seven more days I will cause it to rain on the earth forty
        days and forty nights, and I will destroy from the face of the earth all
        living things that I have made.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And Noah did according to all that the Lord commanded him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: Noah was  six hundred years old when the floodwaters were on the earth.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "So Noah, with his sons, his wife, and his sons\u2019 wives, went
        into the ark because of the waters of the flood. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Of clean animals, of animals that are unclean, of birds, and of everything
        that creeps on the earth, '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'two by two they went into the ark to Noah, male and female, as God
        had commanded Noah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And it came to pass after seven days that the waters of the flood
        were on the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "In the six hundredth year of Noah\u2019s life, in the second month,
        the seventeenth day of the month, on that day all the fountains of the great
        deep were broken up, and the windows of heaven were opened. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: And the rain was on the earth forty days and forty nights.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "On the very same day Noah and Noah\u2019s sons, Shem, Ham, and Japheth,
        and Noah\u2019s wife and the three wives of his sons with them, entered the
        ark\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'they and every beast after its kind, all cattle after their kind,
        every creeping thing that creeps on the earth after its kind, and every bird
        after its kind, every bird of every sort. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And they went into the ark to Noah, two by two, of all flesh in which
        is the breath of life. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: So those that entered, male and female of all flesh, went in as God
        had commanded him; and the Lord shut him in.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Now the flood was on the earth forty days. The waters increased and
        lifted up the ark, and it rose high above the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'The waters prevailed and greatly increased on the earth, and the
        ark moved about on the surface of the waters. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And the waters prevailed exceedingly on the earth, and all the high
        hills under the whole heaven were covered. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'The waters prevailed fifteen cubits upward, and the mountains were
        covered. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And all flesh died that moved on the earth: birds and cattle and
        beasts and every creeping thing that creeps on the earth, and every man. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'All in whose nostrils was the breath of the spirit of life, all that
        was on the dry land, died. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'So He destroyed all living things which were on the face of the ground:
        both man and cattle, creeping thing and bird of the air. They were destroyed
        from the earth. Only Noah and those who were with him in the ark remained
        alive.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: And the waters prevailed on the earth one hundred and fifty days.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Noah\u2019s Deliverance"
      title: "Noah\u2019s Deliverance"
      number: 1
      content: 'Then God remembered Noah, and every living thing, and all the animals
        that were with him in the ark. And God made a wind to pass over the earth,
        and the waters subsided. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'The fountains of the deep and the windows of heaven were also stopped,
        and the rain from heaven was restrained. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And the waters receded continually from the earth. At the end of
        the hundred and fifty days the waters decreased. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Then the ark rested in the seventh month, the seventeenth day of
        the month, on the mountains of Ararat. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: And the waters decreased continually until the tenth month. In the
        tenth month, on the first day of the month, the tops of the mountains were
        seen.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'So it came to pass, at the end of forty days, that Noah opened the
        window of the ark which he had made. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Then he sent out a raven, which kept going to and fro until the waters
        had dried up from the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'He also sent out from himself a dove, to see if the waters had receded
        from the face of the ground. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'But the dove found no resting place for the sole of her foot, and
        she returned into the ark to him, for the waters were on the face of the
        whole earth. So he put out his hand and took her, and drew her into the ark
        to himself. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And he waited yet another seven days, and again he sent the dove
        out from the ark. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Then the dove came to him in the evening, and behold, a freshly plucked
        olive leaf was in her mouth; and Noah knew that the waters had receded from
        the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: So he waited yet another seven days and sent out the dove, which did
        not return again to him anymore.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And it came to pass in the six hundred and first year, in the first
        month, the first day of the month, that the waters were dried up from the
        earth; and Noah removed the covering of the ark and looked, and indeed the
        surface of the ground was dry. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: And in the second month, on the twenty-seventh day of the month, the
        earth was dried.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Then God spoke to Noah, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CGo out of the ark, you and your wife, and your sons and your
        sons\u2019 wives with you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Bring out with you every living thing of all flesh that is with you:
        birds and cattle and every creeping thing that creeps on the earth, so that
        they may abound on the earth, and be fruitful and multiply on the earth.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "So Noah went out, and his sons and his wife and his sons\u2019 wives
        with him. "
      comments: []
    - name: "19: God\u2019s Covenant with Creation"
      title: "God\u2019s Covenant with Creation"
      number: 19
      content: Every animal, every creeping thing, every bird, and whatever creeps
        on the earth, according to their families, went out of the ark.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Then Noah built an altar to the Lord, and took of every clean animal
        and of every clean bird, and offered burnt offerings on the altar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "And the Lord smelled a soothing aroma. Then the Lord said in His
        heart, \u201CI will never again curse the ground for man\u2019s sake, although
        the imagination of man\u2019s heart is evil from his youth; nor will I again
        destroy every living thing as I have done."
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u201CWhile the earth remains,Seedtime and harvest,Cold and heat,Winter
        and summer,And day and nightShall not cease.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: God\u2019s Promise to Noah"
      title: "God\u2019s Promise to Noah"
      number: 1
      content: "So God blessed Noah and his sons, and said to them: \u201CBe fruitful
        and multiply, and fill the earth. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And the fear of you and the dread of you shall be on every beast
        of the earth, on every bird of the air, on all that move on the earth, and
        on all the fish of the sea. They are given into your hand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Every moving thing that lives shall be food for you. I have given
        you all things, even as the green herbs. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'But you shall not eat flesh with its life, that  is, its blood. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Surely for your lifeblood I will demand a  reckoning;  from the hand
        of every beast I will require it, and from the hand of man. From the hand
        of every man\u2019s brother I will require the life of man."
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CWhoever sheds man\u2019s blood,By man his blood shall be shed;For
        in the image of GodHe made man."
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And as for you, be fruitful and multiply;Bring forth abundantly in
        the earthAnd multiply in it.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Then God spoke to Noah and to his sons with him, saying: '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CAnd as for Me, behold, I establish My covenant with you and
        with your descendants after you, "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'and with every living creature that is with you: the birds, the cattle,
        and every beast of the earth with you, of all that go out of the ark, every
        beast of the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Thus I establish My covenant with you: Never again shall all flesh
        be cut off by the waters of the flood; never again shall there be a flood
        to destroy the earth.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And God said: \u201CThis is the sign of the covenant which I make
        between Me and you, and every living creature that is with you, for perpetual
        generations: "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'I set My rainbow in the cloud, and it shall be for the sign of the
        covenant between Me and the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'It shall be, when I bring a cloud over the earth, that the rainbow
        shall be seen in the cloud; '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'and I will remember My covenant which is between Me and you and every
        living creature of all flesh; the waters shall never again become a flood
        to destroy all flesh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "The rainbow shall be in the cloud, and I will look on it to remember
        the everlasting covenant between God and every living creature of all flesh
        that is on the earth.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: Noah and His Sons'
      title: Noah and His Sons
      number: 17
      content: "And God said to Noah, \u201CThis is the sign of the covenant which
        I have established between Me and all flesh that is on the earth.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Now the sons of Noah who went out of the ark were Shem, Ham, and
        Japheth. And Ham was the father of Canaan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: These three were the sons of Noah, and from these the whole earth
        was populated.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And Noah began to  be  a farmer, and he planted a vineyard. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Then he drank of the wine and was drunk, and became uncovered in
        his tent. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And Ham, the father of Canaan, saw the nakedness of his father, and
        told his two brothers outside. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "But Shem and Japheth took a garment, laid it on both their shoulders,
        and went backward and covered the nakedness of their father. Their faces
        were turned away, and they did not see their father\u2019s nakedness."
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'So Noah awoke from his wine, and knew what his younger son had done
        to him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Then he said:\u201CCursed be Canaan;A servant of servantsHe shall
        be to his brethren.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "And he said:\u201CBlessed be the Lord,The God of Shem,And may Canaan
        be his servant."
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "May God enlarge Japheth,And may he dwell in the tents of Shem;And
        may Canaan be his servant.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'And Noah lived after the flood three hundred and fifty years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: So all the days of Noah were nine hundred and fifty years; and he
        died.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Nations Descended from Noah'
      title: Nations Descended from Noah
      number: 1
      content: 'Now this is the genealogy of the sons of Noah: Shem, Ham, and Japheth.
        And sons were born to them after the flood.'
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'The sons of Japheth were Gomer, Magog, Madai, Javan, Tubal, Meshech,
        and Tiras. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'The sons of Gomer were Ashkenaz, Riphath, and Togarmah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'The sons of Javan were Elishah, Tarshish, Kittim, and Dodanim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: From these the coastland peoples of the Gentiles were separated into
        their lands, everyone according to his language, according to their families,
        into their nations.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'The sons of Ham were Cush, Mizraim, Put, and Canaan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: The sons of Cush were Seba, Havilah, Sabtah, Raamah, and Sabtechah;
        and the sons of Raamah were Sheba and Dedan.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Cush begot Nimrod; he began to be a mighty one on the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "He was a mighty hunter before the Lord; therefore it is said, \u201CLike
        Nimrod the mighty hunter before the Lord.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And the beginning of his kingdom was Babel, Erech, Accad, and Calneh,
        in the land of Shinar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'From that land he went to Assyria and built Nineveh, Rehoboth Ir,
        Calah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: and Resen between Nineveh and Calah (that is the principal city).
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Mizraim begot Ludim, Anamim, Lehabim, Naphtuhim, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: Pathrusim, and Casluhim (from whom came the Philistines and Caphtorim).
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Canaan begot Sidon his firstborn, and Heth; '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'the Jebusite, the Amorite, and the Girgashite; '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'the Hivite, the Arkite, and the Sinite; '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'the Arvadite, the Zemarite, and the Hamathite. Afterward the families
        of the Canaanites were dispersed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And the border of the Canaanites was from Sidon as you go toward
        Gerar, as far as Gaza; then as you go toward Sodom, Gomorrah, Admah, and
        Zeboiim, as far as Lasha. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: These were the sons of Ham, according to their families, according
        to their languages, in their lands and in their nations.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And children were born also to Shem, the father of all the children
        of Eber, the brother of Japheth the elder. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'The sons of Shem were Elam, Asshur, Arphaxad, Lud, and Aram. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'The sons of Aram were Uz, Hul, Gether, and Mash. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Arphaxad begot Salah, and Salah begot Eber. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "To Eber were born two sons: the name of one was Peleg, for in his
        days the earth was divided; and his brother\u2019s name was Joktan. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Joktan begot Almodad, Sheleph, Hazarmaveth, Jerah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Hadoram, Uzal, Diklah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Obal, Abimael, Sheba, '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Ophir, Havilah, and Jobab. All these were the sons of Joktan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'And their dwelling place was from Mesha as you go toward Sephar,
        the mountain of the east. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: These were the sons of Shem, according to their families, according
        to their languages, in their lands, according to their nations.
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: These were the families of the sons of Noah, according to their generations,
        in their nations; and from these the nations were divided on the earth after
        the flood.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Tower of Babel'
      title: The Tower of Babel
      number: 1
      content: 'Now the whole earth had one language and one speech. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And it came to pass, as they journeyed from the east, that they found
        a plain in the land of Shinar, and they dwelt there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then they said to one another, \u201CCome, let us make bricks and
        bake them thoroughly.\u201D They had brick for stone, and they had asphalt
        for mortar. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And they said, \u201CCome, let us build ourselves a city, and a tower
        whose top is in the heavens; let us make a name for ourselves, lest we be
        scattered abroad over the face of the whole earth.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'But the Lord came down to see the city and the tower which the sons
        of men had built. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And the Lord said, \u201CIndeed the people are one and they all have
        one language, and this is what they begin to do; now nothing that they propose
        to do will be withheld from them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Come, let Us go down and there confuse their language, that they
        may not understand one another\u2019s speech.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'So the Lord scattered them abroad from there over the face of all
        the earth, and they ceased building the city. '
      comments: []
    - name: "9: Shem\u2019s Descendants"
      title: "Shem\u2019s Descendants"
      number: 9
      content: Therefore its name is called Babel, because there the Lord confused
        the language of all the earth; and from there the Lord scattered them abroad
        over the face of all the earth.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'This is the genealogy of Shem: Shem was one hundred years old, and
        begot Arphaxad two years after the flood. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: After he begot Arphaxad, Shem lived five hundred years, and begot
        sons and daughters.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Arphaxad lived thirty-five years, and begot Salah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: After he begot Salah, Arphaxad lived four hundred and three years,
        and begot sons and daughters.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Salah lived thirty years, and begot Eber. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: After he begot Eber, Salah lived four hundred and three years, and
        begot sons and daughters.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Eber lived thirty-four years, and begot Peleg. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: After he begot Peleg, Eber lived four hundred and thirty years, and
        begot sons and daughters.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Peleg lived thirty years, and begot Reu. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: After he begot Reu, Peleg lived two hundred and nine years, and begot
        sons and daughters.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Reu lived thirty-two years, and begot Serug. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: After he begot Serug, Reu lived two hundred and seven years, and begot
        sons and daughters.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Serug lived thirty years, and begot Nahor. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: After he begot Nahor, Serug lived two hundred years, and begot sons
        and daughters.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Nahor lived twenty-nine years, and begot Terah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: After he begot Terah, Nahor lived one hundred and nineteen years,
        and begot sons and daughters.
      comments: []
    - name: "26: Terah\u2019s Descendants"
      title: "Terah\u2019s Descendants"
      number: 26
      content: Now Terah lived seventy years, and begot Abram, Nahor, and Haran.
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'This is the genealogy of Terah: Terah begot Abram, Nahor, and Haran.
        Haran begot Lot. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'And Haran died before his father Terah in his native land, in Ur
        of the Chaldeans. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Then Abram and Nahor took wives: the name of Abram\u2019s wife was 
        Sarai, and the name of Nahor\u2019s wife, Milcah, the daughter of Haran the
        father of Milcah and the father of Iscah. "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: But Sarai was barren; she had no child.
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "And Terah took his son Abram and his grandson Lot, the son of Haran,
        and his daughter-in-law Sarai, his son Abram\u2019s wife, and they went out
        with them from Ur of the Chaldeans to go to the land of Canaan; and they
        came to Haran and dwelt there. "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: So the days of Terah were two hundred and five years, and Terah died
        in Haran.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Promises to Abram'
      title: Promises to Abram
      number: 1
      content: "Now the Lord had said to Abram:\u201CGet out of your country,From
        your familyAnd from your father\u2019s house,To a land that I will show you."
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: I will make you a great nation;I will bless youAnd make your name
        great;And you shall be a blessing.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "I will bless those who bless you,And I will curse him who curses
        you;And in you all the families of the earth shall be blessed.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'So Abram departed as the Lord had spoken to him, and Lot went with
        him. And Abram was seventy-five years old when he departed from Haran. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then Abram took Sarai his wife and Lot his brother\u2019s son, and
        all their possessions that they had gathered, and the people whom they had
        acquired in Haran, and they departed to go to the land of Canaan. So they
        came to the land of Canaan. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: Abram passed through the land to the place of Shechem, as far as the
        terebinth tree of Moreh. And the Canaanites were then in the land.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Then the Lord appeared to Abram and said, \u201CTo your descendants
        I will give this land.\u201D And there he built an altar to the Lord, who
        had appeared to him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And he moved from there to the mountain east of Bethel, and he pitched
        his tent with Bethel on the west and Ai on the east; there he built an altar
        to the Lord and called on the name of the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: Abram in Egypt'
      title: Abram in Egypt
      number: 9
      content: So Abram journeyed, going on still toward the South.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Now there was a famine in the land, and Abram went down to Egypt
        to dwell there, for the famine was  severe in the land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And it came to pass, when he was close to entering Egypt, that he
        said to Sarai his wife, \u201CIndeed I know that you are  a woman of beautiful
        countenance. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Therefore it will happen, when the Egyptians see you, that they will
        say, \u2018This is his wife\u2019; and they will kill me, but they will let
        you live. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Please say you are my sister, that it may be well with me for your
        sake, and that I may live because of you.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'So it was, when Abram came into Egypt, that the Egyptians saw the
        woman, that she was very beautiful. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "The princes of Pharaoh also saw her and commended her to Pharaoh.
        And the woman was taken to Pharaoh\u2019s house. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: He treated Abram well for her sake. He had sheep, oxen, male donkeys,
        male and female servants, female donkeys, and camels.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "But the Lord  plagued Pharaoh and his house with great plagues because
        of Sarai, Abram\u2019s wife. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And Pharaoh called Abram and said, \u201CWhat is this you have done
        to me? Why did you not tell me that she was your wife? "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Why did you say, \u2018She is my sister\u2019? I might have taken
        her as my wife. Now therefore, here is your wife; take her and go your way.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: So Pharaoh commanded his men concerning him; and they sent him away,
        with his wife and all that he had.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Abram Inherits Canaan'
      title: Abram Inherits Canaan
      number: 1
      content: 'Then Abram went up from Egypt, he and his wife and all that he had,
        and Lot with him, to the South. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Abram was very rich in livestock, in silver, and in gold. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And he went on his journey from the South as far as Bethel, to the
        place where his tent had been at the beginning, between Bethel and Ai, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: to the place of the altar which he had made there at first. And there
        Abram called on the name of the Lord.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Lot also, who went with Abram, had flocks and herds and tents. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Now the land was not able to support them, that they might dwell
        together, for their possessions were so great that they could not dwell together. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And there was strife between the herdsmen of Abram\u2019s livestock
        and the herdsmen of Lot\u2019s livestock. The Canaanites and the Perizzites
        then dwelt in the land."
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "So Abram said to Lot, \u201CPlease let there be no strife between
        you and me, and between my herdsmen and your herdsmen; for we are brethren. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Is not the whole land before you? Please separate from me. If you 
        take the left, then I will go to the right; or, if you  go to the right,
        then I will go to the left.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And Lot lifted his eyes and saw all the plain of Jordan, that it
        was well watered everywhere (before the Lord  destroyed Sodom and Gomorrah)
        like the garden of the Lord, like the land of Egypt as you go toward Zoar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Then Lot chose for himself all the plain of Jordan, and Lot journeyed
        east. And they separated from each other. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Abram dwelt in the land of Canaan, and Lot dwelt in the cities of
        the plain and pitched his tent even as far as Sodom. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: But the men of Sodom were exceedingly wicked and sinful against the
        Lord.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And the Lord said to Abram, after Lot had separated from him: \u201CLift
        your eyes now and look from the place where you are\u2014northward, southward,
        eastward, and westward; "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'for all the land which you see I give to you and your descendants
        forever. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And I will make your descendants as the dust of the earth; so that
        if a man could number the dust of the earth, then your descendants also could
        be numbered. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Arise, walk in the land through its length and its width, for I give
        it to you.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: Then Abram moved his tent, and went and dwelt by the terebinth trees
        of Mamre, which are in Hebron, and built an altar there to the Lord.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Lot\u2019s Captivity and Rescue"
      title: "Lot\u2019s Captivity and Rescue"
      number: 1
      content: 'And it came to pass in the days of Amraphel king of Shinar, Arioch
        king of Ellasar, Chedorlaomer king of Elam, and Tidal king of nations, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'that they made war with Bera king of Sodom, Birsha king of Gomorrah,
        Shinab king of Admah, Shemeber king of Zeboiim, and the king of Bela (that
        is, Zoar). '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'All these joined together in the Valley of Siddim (that is, the Salt
        Sea). '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: Twelve years they served Chedorlaomer, and in the thirteenth year
        they rebelled.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'In the fourteenth year Chedorlaomer and the kings that were with
        him came and attacked the Rephaim in Ashteroth Karnaim, the Zuzim in Ham,
        the Emim in Shaveh Kiriathaim, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'and the Horites in their mountain of Seir, as far as El Paran, which
        is by the wilderness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: Then they turned back and came to En Mishpat (that is, Kadesh), and
        attacked all the country of the Amalekites, and also the Amorites who dwelt
        in Hazezon Tamar.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And the king of Sodom, the king of Gomorrah, the king of Admah, the
        king of Zeboiim, and the king of Bela (that is, Zoar) went out and joined
        together in battle in the Valley of Siddim '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "against Chedorlaomer king of Elam, Tidal king of nations, Amraphel
        king of Shinar, and Arioch king of Ellasar\u2014four kings against five. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Now the Valley of Siddim was  full  of  asphalt pits; and the kings
        of Sodom and Gomorrah fled; some fell there, and the remainder fled to the
        mountains. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Then they took all the goods of Sodom and Gomorrah, and all their
        provisions, and went their way. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "They also took Lot, Abram\u2019s brother\u2019s son who dwelt in
        Sodom, and his goods, and departed."
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Then one who had escaped came and told Abram the Hebrew, for he dwelt
        by the terebinth trees of Mamre the Amorite, brother of Eshcol and brother
        of Aner; and they were allies with Abram. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Now when Abram heard that his brother was taken captive, he armed
        his three hundred and eighteen trained servants who were born in his own
        house, and went in pursuit as far as Dan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'He divided his forces against them by night, and he and his servants
        attacked them and pursued them as far as Hobah, which is north of Damascus. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: So he brought back all the goods, and also brought back his brother
        Lot and his goods, as well as the women and the people.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: Abram and Melchizedek'
      title: Abram and Melchizedek
      number: 17
      content: "And the king of Sodom went out to meet him at the Valley of Shaveh
        (that is,  the King\u2019s Valley), after his return from the defeat of Chedorlaomer
        and the kings who were with him."
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Then Melchizedek king of Salem brought out bread and wine; he was 
        the priest of God Most High. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And he blessed him and said:\u201CBlessed be Abram of God Most High,Possessor
        of heaven and earth;"
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And blessed be God Most High,Who has delivered your enemies into
        your hand.\u201DAnd he gave him a tithe of all."
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Now the king of Sodom said to Abram, \u201CGive me the persons, and
        take the goods for yourself.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "But Abram said to the king of Sodom, \u201CI have raised my hand
        to the Lord, God Most High, the Possessor of heaven and earth, "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "that I will  take nothing, from a thread to a sandal strap, and that
        I will not take anything that is yours, lest you should say, \u2018I have
        made Abram rich\u2019\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "except only what the young men have eaten, and the portion of the
        men who went with me: Aner, Eshcol, and Mamre; let them take their portion.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: God\u2019s Covenant with Abram"
      title: "God\u2019s Covenant with Abram"
      number: 1
      content: "After these things the word of the Lord came to Abram in a vision,
        saying, \u201CDo not be afraid, Abram. I am your shield, your exceedingly
        great reward.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "But Abram said, \u201CLord God, what will You give me, seeing I go
        childless, and the heir of my house is Eliezer of Damascus?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then Abram said, \u201CLook, You have given me no offspring; indeed
        one born in my house is my heir!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And behold, the word of the Lord  came to him, saying, \u201CThis
        one shall not be your heir, but one who will come from your own body shall
        be your heir.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then He brought him outside and said, \u201CLook now toward heaven,
        and count the stars if you are able to number them.\u201D And He said to
        him, \u201CSo shall your descendants be.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: And he believed in the Lord, and He accounted it to him for righteousness.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Then He said to him, \u201CI am the Lord, who brought you out of
        Ur of the Chaldeans, to give you this land to inherit it.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And he said, \u201CLord God, how shall I know that I will inherit
        it?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "So He said to him, \u201CBring Me a three-year-old heifer, a three-year-old
        female goat, a three-year-old ram, a turtledove, and a young pigeon.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Then he brought all these to Him and cut them in two, down the middle,
        and placed each piece opposite the other; but he did not cut the birds in
        two. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: And when the vultures came down on the carcasses, Abram drove them
        away.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Now when the sun was going down, a deep sleep fell upon Abram; and
        behold, horror and great darkness fell upon him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then He said to Abram: \u201CKnow certainly that your descendants
        will be strangers in a land that  is not theirs, and will serve them, and
        they will afflict them four hundred years. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And also the nation whom they serve I will judge; afterward they
        shall come out with great possessions. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Now as for you, you shall go to your fathers in peace; you shall
        be buried at a good old age. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "But in the fourth generation they shall return here, for the iniquity
        of the Amorites is not yet complete.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And it came to pass, when the sun went down and it was dark, that
        behold, there appeared a smoking oven and a burning torch that passed between
        those pieces. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "On the same day the Lord  made a covenant with Abram, saying:\u201CTo
        your descendants I have given this land, from the river of Egypt to the great
        river, the River Euphrates\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'the Kenites, the Kenezzites, the Kadmonites, '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'the Hittites, the Perizzites, the Rephaim, '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "the Amorites, the Canaanites, the Girgashites, and the Jebusites.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Hagar and Ishmael'
      title: Hagar and Ishmael
      number: 1
      content: "Now Sarai, Abram\u2019s wife, had borne him no children. And she
        had an Egyptian maidservant whose name was Hagar. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "So Sarai said to Abram, \u201CSee now, the Lord  has restrained me
        from bearing children. Please, go in to my maid; perhaps I shall obtain children
        by her.\u201D And Abram heeded the voice of Sarai. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then Sarai, Abram\u2019s wife, took Hagar her maid, the Egyptian,
        and gave her to her husband Abram to be his wife, after Abram had dwelt ten
        years in the land of Canaan. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: So he went in to Hagar, and she conceived. And when she saw that she
        had conceived, her mistress became despised in her eyes.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then Sarai said to Abram, \u201CMy wrong be upon you! I gave my maid
        into your embrace; and when she saw that she had conceived, I became despised
        in her eyes. The Lord judge between you and me.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "So Abram said to Sarai, \u201CIndeed your maid is in your hand; do
        to her as you please.\u201D And when Sarai dealt harshly with her, she fled
        from her presence."
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Now the Angel of the Lord found her by a spring of water in the wilderness,
        by the spring on the way to Shur. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And He said, \u201CHagar, Sarai\u2019s maid, where have you come
        from, and where are you going?\u201DShe said, \u201CI am fleeing from the
        presence of my mistress Sarai.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "The Angel of the Lord said to her, \u201CReturn to your mistress,
        and submit yourself under her hand.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then the Angel of the Lord said to her, \u201CI will multiply your
        descendants exceedingly, so that they shall not be counted for multitude.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And the Angel of the Lord said to her:\u201CBehold, you are with
        child,And you shall bear a son.You shall call his name Ishmael,Because the
        Lord has heard your affliction."
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "He shall be a wild man;His hand shall  be against every man,And every
        man\u2019s hand against him.And he shall dwell in the presence of all his
        brethren.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then she called the name of the Lord who spoke to her, You-Are-the-God-Who-Sees;
        for she said, \u201CHave I also here seen Him who sees me?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: Therefore the well was called Beer Lahai Roi; observe, it  is  between
        Kadesh and Bered.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'So Hagar bore Abram a son; and Abram named his son, whom Hagar bore,
        Ishmael. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: Abram was eighty-six years old when Hagar bore Ishmael to Abram.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Sign of the Covenant'
      title: The Sign of the Covenant
      number: 1
      content: "When Abram was ninety-nine years old, the Lord  appeared to Abram
        and said to him, \u201CI am Almighty God; walk before Me and be blameless. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And I will make My covenant between Me and you, and will multiply
        you exceedingly.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Then Abram fell on his face, and God talked with him, saying: '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CAs for Me, behold, My covenant is with you, and you shall be
        a father of many nations. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'No longer shall your name be called Abram, but your name shall be
        Abraham; for I have made you a father of many nations. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'I will make you exceedingly fruitful; and I will make nations of
        you, and kings shall come from you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And I will establish My covenant between Me and you and your descendants
        after you in their generations, for an everlasting covenant, to be God to
        you and your descendants after you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Also I give to you and your descendants after you the land in which
        you are a stranger, all the land of Canaan, as an everlasting possession;
        and I will be their God.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And God said to Abraham: \u201CAs for you, you shall keep My covenant,
        you and your descendants after you throughout their generations. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'This is My covenant which you shall keep, between Me and you and
        your descendants after you: Every male child among you shall be circumcised; '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'and you shall be circumcised in the flesh of your foreskins, and
        it shall be a sign of the covenant between Me and you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'He who is eight days old among you shall be circumcised, every male
        child in your generations, he who is born in your house or bought with money
        from any foreigner who is not your descendant. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'He who is born in your house and he who is bought with your money
        must be circumcised, and My covenant shall be in your flesh for an everlasting
        covenant. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And the uncircumcised male child, who is not circumcised in the flesh
        of his foreskin, that person shall be cut off from his people; he has broken
        My covenant.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Then God said to Abraham, \u201CAs for Sarai your wife, you shall
        not call her name Sarai, but Sarah shall  be her name. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And I will bless her and also give you a son by her; then I will
        bless her, and she shall be a  mother  of nations; kings of peoples shall
        be from her.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Then Abraham fell on his face and laughed, and said in his heart,
        \u201CShall a  child be born to a man who is one hundred years old? And shall
        Sarah, who is ninety years old, bear a  child?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And Abraham said to God, \u201COh, that Ishmael might live before
        You!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Then God said: \u201CNo, Sarah your wife shall bear you a son, and
        you shall call his name Isaac; I will establish My covenant with him for
        an everlasting covenant, and with his descendants after him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And as for Ishmael, I have heard you. Behold, I have blessed him,
        and will make him fruitful, and will multiply him exceedingly. He shall beget
        twelve princes, and I will make him a great nation. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "But My covenant I will establish with Isaac, whom Sarah shall bear
        to you at this set time next year.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: Then He finished talking with him, and God went up from Abraham.
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "So Abraham took Ishmael his son, all who were born in his house and
        all who were bought with his money, every male among the men of Abraham\u2019s
        house, and circumcised the flesh of their foreskins that very same day, as
        God had said to him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Abraham was ninety-nine years old when he was circumcised in the
        flesh of his foreskin. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'And Ishmael his son was thirteen years old when he was circumcised
        in the flesh of his foreskin. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'That very same day Abraham was circumcised, and his son Ishmael; '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: and all the men of his house, born in the house or bought with money
        from a foreigner, were circumcised with him.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Son of Promise'
      title: The Son of Promise
      number: 1
      content: 'Then the Lord appeared to him by the terebinth trees of Mamre, as
        he was sitting in the tent door in the heat of the day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'So he lifted his eyes and looked, and behold, three men were standing
        by him; and when he saw them, he ran from the tent door to meet them, and
        bowed himself to the ground, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "and said, \u201CMy Lord, if I have now found favor in Your sight,
        do not pass on by Your servant. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Please let a little water be brought, and wash your feet, and rest
        yourselves under the tree. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And I will bring a morsel of bread, that you may refresh your hearts.
        After that you may pass by, inasmuch as you have come to your servant.\u201DThey
        said, \u201CDo as you have said.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "So Abraham hurried into the tent to Sarah and said, \u201CQuickly,
        make ready three measures of fine meal; knead it and make cakes.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And Abraham ran to the herd, took a tender and good calf, gave it
        to a young man, and he hastened to prepare it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: So he took butter and milk and the calf which he had prepared, and
        set it before them; and he stood by them under the tree as they ate.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then they said to him, \u201CWhere is Sarah your wife?\u201DSo he
        said, \u201CHere, in the tent.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And He said, \u201CI will certainly return to you according to the
        time of life, and behold, Sarah your wife shall have a son.\u201D(Sarah was
        listening in the tent door which was behind him.) "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Now Abraham and Sarah were old, well advanced in age; and Sarah had
        passed the age of childbearing. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Therefore Sarah laughed within herself, saying, \u201CAfter I have
        grown old, shall I have pleasure, my lord being old also?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And the Lord said to Abraham, \u201CWhy did Sarah laugh, saying,
        \u2018Shall I surely bear a  child, since I am old?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Is anything too hard for the Lord? At the appointed time I will return
        to you, according to the time of life, and Sarah shall have a son.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '15: Abraham Intercedes for Sodom'
      title: Abraham Intercedes for Sodom
      number: 15
      content: "But Sarah denied it, saying, \u201CI did not laugh,\u201D for she
        was afraid.And He said, \u201CNo, but you did laugh!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Then the men rose from there and looked toward Sodom, and Abraham
        went with them to send them on the way. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And the Lord said, \u201CShall I hide from Abraham what I am doing, "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'since Abraham shall surely become a great and mighty nation, and
        all the nations of the earth shall be blessed in him? '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "For I have known him, in order that he may command his children and
        his household after him, that they keep the way of the Lord, to do righteousness
        and justice, that the Lord may bring to Abraham what He has spoken to him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And the Lord said, \u201CBecause the outcry against Sodom and Gomorrah
        is great, and because their sin is very grave, "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "I will go down now and see whether they have done altogether according
        to the outcry against it that has come to Me; and if not, I will know.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Then the men turned away from there and went toward Sodom, but Abraham
        still stood before the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "And Abraham came near and said, \u201CWould You also destroy the
        righteous with the wicked? "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Suppose there were fifty righteous within the city; would You also
        destroy the place and not spare it for the fifty righteous that were in it? '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Far be it from You to do such a thing as this, to slay the righteous
        with the wicked, so that the righteous should be as the wicked; far be it
        from You! Shall not the Judge of all the earth do right?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "So the Lord said, \u201CIf I find in Sodom fifty righteous within
        the city, then I will spare all the place for their sakes.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Then Abraham answered and said, \u201CIndeed now, I who am  but dust
        and ashes have taken it upon myself to speak to the Lord: "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Suppose there were five less than the fifty righteous; would You
        destroy all of the city for lack  of five?\u201DSo He said, \u201CIf I find
        there forty-five, I will not destroy it.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "And he spoke to Him yet again and said, \u201CSuppose there should
        be forty found there?\u201DSo He said, \u201CI will not do it for the sake
        of forty.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Then he said, \u201CLet not the Lord be angry, and I will speak:
        Suppose thirty should be found there?\u201DSo He said, \u201CI will not do
        it if I find thirty there.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "And he said, \u201CIndeed now, I have taken it upon myself to speak
        to the Lord: Suppose twenty should be found there?\u201DSo He said, \u201CI
        will not destroy it for the sake of twenty.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "Then he said, \u201CLet not the Lord be angry, and I will speak but
        once more: Suppose ten should be found there?\u201DAnd He said, \u201CI will
        not destroy it for the sake of ten.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: So the Lord went His way as soon as He had finished speaking with
        Abraham; and Abraham returned to his place.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Sodom\u2019s Depravity"
      title: "Sodom\u2019s Depravity"
      number: 1
      content: 'Now the two angels came to Sodom in the evening, and Lot was sitting
        in the gate of Sodom. When Lot saw them, he rose to meet them, and he bowed
        himself with his face toward the ground. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And he said, \u201CHere now, my lords, please turn in to your servant\u2019s
        house and spend the night, and wash your feet; then you may rise early and
        go on your way.\u201DAnd they said, \u201CNo, but we will spend the night
        in the open square.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: But he insisted strongly; so they turned in to him and entered his
        house. Then he made them a feast, and baked unleavened bread, and they ate.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Now before they lay down, the men of the city, the men of Sodom,
        both old and young, all the people from every quarter, surrounded the house. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And they called to Lot and said to him, \u201CWhere are the men who
        came to you tonight? Bring them out to us that we may know them carnally.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'So Lot went out to them through the doorway, shut the door behind
        him, '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "and said, \u201CPlease, my brethren, do not do so wickedly! "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "See now, I have two daughters who have not known a man; please, let
        me bring them out to you, and you may do to them as you wish; only do nothing
        to these men, since this is the reason they have come under the shadow of
        my roof.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And they said, \u201CStand back!\u201D Then they said, \u201CThis
        one came in to stay here,  and he keeps acting as a judge; now we will deal
        worse with you than with them.\u201D So they pressed hard against the man
        Lot, and came near to break down the door. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'But the men reached out their hands and pulled Lot into the house
        with them, and shut the door. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: Sodom and Gomorrah Destroyed'
      title: Sodom and Gomorrah Destroyed
      number: 11
      content: And they struck the men who were at the doorway of the house with
        blindness, both small and great, so that they became weary trying to find
        the door.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then the men said to Lot, \u201CHave you anyone else here? Son-in-law,
        your sons, your daughters, and whomever you have in the city\u2014take them
        out of this place! "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "For we will destroy this place, because the outcry against them has
        grown great before the face of the Lord, and the Lord has sent us to destroy
        it.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "So Lot went out and spoke to his sons-in-law, who had married his
        daughters, and said, \u201CGet up, get out of this place; for the Lord will
        destroy this city!\u201D But to his sons-in-law he seemed to be joking."
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "When the morning dawned, the angels urged Lot to hurry, saying, \u201CArise,
        take your wife and your two daughters who are here, lest you be consumed
        in the punishment of the city.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And while he lingered, the men took hold of his hand, his wife\u2019s
        hand, and the hands of his two daughters, the Lord being merciful to him,
        and they brought him out and set him outside the city. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "So it came to pass, when they had brought them outside, that he said,
        \u201CEscape for your life! Do not look behind you nor stay anywhere in the
        plain. Escape to the mountains, lest you be destroyed.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Then Lot said to them, \u201CPlease, no, my lords! "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Indeed now, your servant has found favor in your sight, and you have
        increased your mercy which you have shown me by saving my life; but I cannot
        escape to the mountains, lest some evil overtake me and I die. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "See now, this city is near enough to flee to, and it is a little
        one; please let me escape there (is it not a little one?) and my soul shall
        live.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "And he said to him, \u201CSee, I have favored you concerning this
        thing also, in that I will not overthrow this city for which you have spoken. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Hurry, escape there. For I cannot do anything until you arrive there.\u201DTherefore
        the name of the city was called Zoar."
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'The sun had risen upon the earth when Lot entered Zoar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Then the Lord rained brimstone and fire on Sodom and Gomorrah, from
        the Lord out of the heavens. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: So He overthrew those cities, all the plain, all the inhabitants of
        the cities, and what grew on the ground.
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: But his wife looked back behind him, and she became a pillar of salt.
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'And Abraham went early in the morning to the place where he had stood
        before the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Then he looked toward Sodom and Gomorrah, and toward all the land
        of the plain; and he saw, and behold, the smoke of the land which went up
        like the smoke of a furnace. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: The Descendants of Lot'
      title: The Descendants of Lot
      number: 29
      content: And it came to pass, when God destroyed the cities of the plain, that
        God remembered Abraham, and sent Lot out of the midst of the overthrow, when
        He overthrew the cities in which Lot had dwelt.
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Then Lot went up out of Zoar and dwelt in the mountains, and his
        two daughters were with him; for he was afraid to dwell in Zoar. And he and
        his two daughters dwelt in a cave. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Now the firstborn said to the younger, \u201COur father is old, and
        there  is no man on the earth to come in to us as is the custom of all the
        earth. "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "Come, let us make our father drink wine, and we will lie with him,
        that we may preserve the lineage of our father.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: So they made their father drink wine that night. And the firstborn
        went in and lay with her father, and he did not know when she lay down or
        when she arose.
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "It happened on the next day that the firstborn said to the younger,
        \u201CIndeed I lay with my father last night; let us make him drink wine
        tonight also, and you go in and lie with him, that we may preserve the lineage
        of our father.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: Then they made their father drink wine that night also. And the younger
        arose and lay with him, and he did not know when she lay down or when she
        arose.
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'Thus both the daughters of Lot were with child by their father. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'The firstborn bore a son and called his name Moab; he is the father
        of the Moabites to this day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: And the younger, she also bore a son and called his name Ben-Ammi;
        he is the father of the people of Ammon to this day.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Abraham and Abimelech'
      title: Abraham and Abimelech
      number: 1
      content: 'And Abraham journeyed from there to the South, and dwelt between
        Kadesh and Shur, and stayed in Gerar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Now Abraham said of Sarah his wife, \u201CShe is my sister.\u201D
        And Abimelech king of Gerar sent and took Sarah."
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "But God came to Abimelech in a dream by night, and said to him, \u201CIndeed
        you are a dead man because of the woman whom you have taken, for she is a
        man\u2019s wife.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "But Abimelech had not come near her; and he said, \u201CLord, will
        You slay a righteous nation also? "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Did he not say to me, \u2018She is my sister\u2019? And she, even
        she herself said, \u2018He is my brother.\u2019 In the integrity of my heart
        and innocence of my hands I have done this.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And God said to him in a dream, \u201CYes, I know that you did this
        in the integrity of your heart. For I also withheld you from sinning against
        Me; therefore I did not let you touch her. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Now therefore, restore the man\u2019s wife; for he is a prophet,
        and he will pray for you and you shall live. But if you do not restore her, 
        know that you shall surely die, you and all who are yours.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'So Abimelech rose early in the morning, called all his servants,
        and told all these things in their hearing; and the men were very much afraid. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And Abimelech called Abraham and said to him, \u201CWhat have you
        done to us? How have I offended you, that you have brought on me and on my
        kingdom a great sin? You have done deeds to me that ought not to be done.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then Abimelech said to Abraham, \u201CWhat did you have in view,
        that you have done this thing?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And Abraham said, \u201CBecause I thought, surely the fear of God
        is not in this place; and they will kill me on account of my wife. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'But indeed she  is truly my sister. She is the daughter of my father,
        but not the daughter of my mother; and she became my wife. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And it came to pass, when God caused me to wander from my father\u2019s
        house, that I said to her, \u2018This is your kindness that you should do
        for me: in every place, wherever we go, say of me, \u201CHe is my brother.\u201D
        \u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Then Abimelech took sheep, oxen, and male and female servants, and
        gave them to Abraham; and he restored Sarah his wife to him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And Abimelech said, \u201CSee, my land is before you; dwell where
        it pleases you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Then to Sarah he said, \u201CBehold, I have given your brother a
        thousand pieces of silver; indeed this vindicates you before all who are
        with you and before everybody.\u201D Thus she was rebuked."
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'So Abraham prayed to God; and God healed Abimelech, his wife, and
        his female servants. Then they bore children;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "for the Lord  had closed up all the wombs of the house of Abimelech
        because of Sarah, Abraham\u2019s wife."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Isaac Is Born'
      title: Isaac Is Born
      number: 1
      content: 'And the Lord  visited Sarah as He had said, and the Lord did for
        Sarah as He had spoken. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'For Sarah conceived and bore Abraham a son in his old age, at the
        set time of which God had spoken to him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And Abraham called the name of his son who was born to him\u2014whom
        Sarah bore to him\u2014Isaac. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Then Abraham circumcised his son Isaac when he was eight days old,
        as God had commanded him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Now Abraham was one hundred years old when his son Isaac was born
        to him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And Sarah said, \u201CGod has made me laugh, and all who hear will
        laugh with me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: Hagar and Ishmael Depart'
      title: Hagar and Ishmael Depart
      number: 7
      content: "She also said, \u201CWho would have said to Abraham that Sarah would
        nurse children? For I have borne him a son in his old age.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: So the child grew and was weaned. And Abraham made a great feast on
        the same day that Isaac was weaned.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And Sarah saw the son of Hagar the Egyptian, whom she had borne to
        Abraham, scoffing. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Therefore she said to Abraham, \u201CCast out this bondwoman and
        her son; for the son of this bondwoman shall not be heir with my son, namely
        with Isaac.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And the matter was very displeasing in Abraham\u2019s sight because
        of his son."
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "But God said to Abraham, \u201CDo not let it be displeasing in your
        sight because of the lad or because of your bondwoman. Whatever Sarah has
        said to you, listen to her voice; for in Isaac your seed shall be called. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Yet I will also make a nation of the son of the bondwoman, because
        he is your seed.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'So Abraham rose early in the morning, and took bread and a skin of
        water; and putting it on her shoulder, he gave it and the boy to Hagar, and
        sent her away. Then she departed and wandered in the Wilderness of Beersheba. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And the water in the skin was used up, and she placed the boy under
        one of the shrubs. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Then she went and sat down across from him at a distance of about
        a bowshot; for she said to herself, \u201CLet me not see the death of the
        boy.\u201D So she sat opposite him, and lifted her voice and wept."
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And God heard the voice of the lad. Then the angel of God called
        to Hagar out of heaven, and said to her, \u201CWhat ails you, Hagar? Fear
        not, for God has heard the voice of the lad where he is.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Arise, lift up the lad and hold him with your hand, for I will make
        him a great nation.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Then God opened her eyes, and she saw a well of water. And she went
        and filled the skin with water, and gave the lad a drink. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'So God was with the lad; and he grew and dwelt in the wilderness,
        and became an archer. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: A Covenant with Abimelech'
      title: A Covenant with Abimelech
      number: 21
      content: He dwelt in the Wilderness of Paran; and his mother took a wife for
        him from the land of Egypt.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "And it came to pass at that time that Abimelech and Phichol, the
        commander of his army, spoke to Abraham, saying, \u201CGod is with you in
        all that you do. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Now therefore, swear to me by God that you will not deal falsely
        with me, with my offspring, or with my posterity; but that according to the
        kindness that I have done to you, you will do to me and to the land in which
        you have dwelt.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "And Abraham said, \u201CI will swear.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Then Abraham rebuked Abimelech because of a well of water which Abimelech\u2019s
        servants had seized. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "And Abimelech said, \u201CI do not know who has done this thing;
        you did not tell me, nor had I heard of  it until today.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'So Abraham took sheep and oxen and gave them to Abimelech, and the
        two of them made a covenant. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: And Abraham set seven ewe lambs of the flock by themselves.
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Then Abimelech asked Abraham, \u201CWhat is  the  meaning  of these
        seven ewe lambs which you have set by themselves?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "And he said, \u201CYou will take these seven ewe lambs from my hand,
        that they may be my witness that I have dug this well.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: Therefore he called that place Beersheba, because the two of them
        swore an oath there.
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Thus they made a covenant at Beersheba. So Abimelech rose with Phichol,
        the commander of his army, and they returned to the land of the Philistines. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'Then Abraham planted a tamarisk tree in Beersheba, and there called
        on the name of the Lord, the Everlasting God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: And Abraham stayed in the land of the Philistines many days.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Abraham\u2019s Faith Confirmed"
      title: "Abraham\u2019s Faith Confirmed"
      number: 1
      content: "Now it came to pass after these things that God tested Abraham, and
        said to him, \u201CAbraham!\u201DAnd he said, \u201CHere I am.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Then He said, \u201CTake now your son, your only son Isaac, whom
        you love, and go to the land of Moriah, and offer him there as a burnt offering
        on one of the mountains of which I shall tell you.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'So Abraham rose early in the morning and saddled his donkey, and
        took two of his young men with him, and Isaac his son; and he split the wood
        for the burnt offering, and arose and went to the place of which God had
        told him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Then on the third day Abraham lifted his eyes and saw the place afar
        off. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And Abraham said to his young men, \u201CStay here with the donkey;
        the lad and I will go yonder and worship, and we will come back to you.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'So Abraham took the wood of the burnt offering and laid it on Isaac
        his son; and he took the fire in his hand, and a knife, and the two of them
        went together. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "But Isaac spoke to Abraham his father and said, \u201CMy father!\u201DAnd
        he said, \u201CHere I am, my son.\u201DThen he said, \u201CLook, the fire
        and the wood, but where is the lamb for a burnt offering?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And Abraham said, \u201CMy son, God will provide for Himself the
        lamb for a burnt offering.\u201D So the two of them went together."
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Then they came to the place of which God had told him. And Abraham
        built an altar there and placed the wood in order; and he bound Isaac his
        son and laid him on the altar, upon the wood. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: And Abraham stretched out his hand and took the knife to slay his
        son.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "But the Angel of the Lord called to him from heaven and said, \u201CAbraham,
        Abraham!\u201DSo he said, \u201CHere I am.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And He said, \u201CDo not lay your hand on the lad, or do anything
        to him; for now I know that you fear God, since you have not withheld your
        son, your only son, from Me.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Then Abraham lifted his eyes and looked, and there behind him  was
        a ram caught in a thicket by its horns. So Abraham went and took the ram,
        and offered it up for a burnt offering instead of his son. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And Abraham called the name of the place, The-Lord-Will-Provide;
        as it is said to this day, \u201CIn the Mount of the Lord it shall be provided.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Then the Angel of the Lord called to Abraham a second time out of
        heaven, '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "and said: \u201CBy Myself I have sworn, says the Lord, because you
        have done this thing, and have not withheld your son, your only son\u2014"
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'blessing I will bless you, and multiplying I will multiply your descendants
        as the stars of the heaven and as the sand which is on the seashore; and
        your descendants shall possess the gate of their enemies. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "In your seed all the nations of the earth shall be blessed, because
        you have obeyed My voice.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: The Family of Nahor'
      title: The Family of Nahor
      number: 19
      content: So Abraham returned to his young men, and they rose and went together
        to Beersheba; and Abraham dwelt at Beersheba.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Now it came to pass after these things that it was told Abraham,
        saying, \u201CIndeed Milcah also has borne children to your brother Nahor: "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Huz his firstborn, Buz his brother, Kemuel the father of Aram, '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Chesed, Hazo, Pildash, Jidlaph, and Bethuel.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "And Bethuel begot Rebekah. These eight Milcah bore to Nahor, Abraham\u2019s
        brother. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: His concubine, whose name was Reumah, also bore Tebah, Gaham, Thahash,
        and Maachah.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Sarah\u2019s Death and Burial"
      title: "Sarah\u2019s Death and Burial"
      number: 1
      content: 'Sarah lived one hundred and twenty-seven years; these  were the years
        of the life of Sarah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: So Sarah died in Kirjath Arba (that is,  Hebron) in the land of Canaan,
        and Abraham came to mourn for Sarah and to weep for her.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Then Abraham stood up from before his dead, and spoke to the sons
        of Heth, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CI am a foreigner and a visitor among you. Give me property
        for a burial place among you, that I may bury my dead out of my sight.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And the sons of Heth answered Abraham, saying to him, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CHear us, my lord: You are a mighty prince among us; bury your
        dead in the choicest of our burial places. None of us will withhold from
        you his burial place, that you may bury your dead.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Then Abraham stood up and bowed himself to the people of the land,
        the sons of Heth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And he spoke with them, saying, \u201CIf it is your wish that I bury
        my dead out of my sight, hear me, and meet with Ephron the son of Zohar for
        me, "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "that he may give me the cave of Machpelah which he has, which is
        at the end of his field. Let him give it to me at the full price, as property
        for a burial place among you.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Now Ephron dwelt among the sons of Heth; and Ephron the Hittite answered
        Abraham in the presence of the sons of Heth, all who entered at the gate
        of his city, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CNo, my lord, hear me: I give you the field and the cave that
        is in it; I give it to you in the presence of the sons of my people. I give
        it to you. Bury your dead!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Then Abraham bowed himself down before the people of the land; '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "and he spoke to Ephron in the hearing of the people of the land,
        saying, \u201CIf you will  give  it, please hear me. I will give you money
        for the field; take it from me and I will bury my dead there.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And Ephron answered Abraham, saying to him, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CMy lord, listen to me; the land is  worth four hundred shekels
        of silver. What is that between you and me? So bury your dead.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: And Abraham listened to Ephron; and Abraham weighed out the silver
        for Ephron which he had named in the hearing of the sons of Heth, four hundred
        shekels of silver, currency of the merchants.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'So the field of Ephron which was in Machpelah, which was before Mamre,
        the field and the cave which was in it, and all the trees that were in the
        field, which were within all the surrounding borders, were deeded '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: to Abraham as a possession in the presence of the sons of Heth, before
        all who went in at the gate of his city.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And after this, Abraham buried Sarah his wife in the cave of the
        field of Machpelah, before Mamre (that is, Hebron) in the land of Canaan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: So the field and the cave that is in it were deeded to Abraham by
        the sons of Heth as property for a burial place.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: A Bride for Isaac'
      title: A Bride for Isaac
      number: 1
      content: 'Now Abraham was old, well advanced in age; and the Lord  had blessed
        Abraham in all things. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "So Abraham said to the oldest servant of his house, who ruled over
        all that he had, \u201CPlease, put your hand under my thigh, "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'and I will make you swear by the Lord, the God of heaven and the
        God of the earth, that you will not take a wife for my son from the daughters
        of the Canaanites, among whom I dwell; '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "but you shall go to my country and to my family, and take a wife
        for my son Isaac.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And the servant said to him, \u201CPerhaps the woman will not be
        willing to follow me to this land. Must I take your son back to the land
        from which you came?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "But Abraham said to him, \u201CBeware that you do not take my son
        back there. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "The Lord God of heaven, who took me from my father\u2019s house and
        from the land of my family, and who spoke to me and swore to me, saying,
        \u2018To your descendants I give this land,\u2019 He will send His angel
        before you, and you shall take a wife for my son from there. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And if the woman is not willing to follow you, then you will be released
        from this oath; only do not take my son back there.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: So the servant put his hand under the thigh of Abraham his master,
        and swore to him concerning this matter.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then the servant took ten of his master\u2019s camels and departed,
        for all his master\u2019s goods were  in his hand. And he arose and went
        to Mesopotamia, to the city of Nahor. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And he made his camels kneel down outside the city by a well of water
        at evening time, the time when women go out to draw water.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then he said, \u201CO Lord God of my master Abraham, please give
        me success this day, and show kindness to my master Abraham. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Behold, here  I stand by the well of water, and the daughters of
        the men of the city are coming out to draw water. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Now let it be that the young woman to whom I say, \u2018Please let
        down your pitcher that I may drink,\u2019 and she says, \u2018Drink, and
        I will also give your camels a drink\u2019\u2014let her be  the  one You
        have appointed for Your servant Isaac. And by this I will know that You have
        shown kindness to my master.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And it happened, before he had finished speaking, that behold, Rebekah,
        who was born to Bethuel, son of Milcah, the wife of Nahor, Abraham\u2019s
        brother, came out with her pitcher on her shoulder. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Now the young woman was very beautiful to behold, a virgin; no man
        had known her. And she went down to the well, filled her pitcher, and came
        up. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And the servant ran to meet her and said, \u201CPlease let me drink
        a little water from your pitcher.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "So she said, \u201CDrink, my lord.\u201D Then she quickly let her
        pitcher down to her hand, and gave him a drink. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And when she had finished giving him a drink, she said, \u201CI will
        draw water for your camels also, until they have finished drinking.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Then she quickly emptied her pitcher into the trough, ran back to
        the well to draw water, and drew for all his camels. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: And the man, wondering at her, remained silent so as to know whether
        the Lord had made his journey prosperous or not.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'So it was, when the camels had finished drinking, that the man took
        a golden nose ring weighing half a shekel, and two bracelets for her wrists
        weighing ten shekels of gold, '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "and said, \u201CWhose daughter are you? Tell me, please, is there
        room in your father\u2019s house for us to lodge?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "So she said to him, \u201CI am the daughter of Bethuel, Milcah\u2019s
        son, whom she bore to Nahor.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Moreover she said to him, \u201CWe have both straw and feed enough,
        and room to lodge.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Then the man bowed down his head and worshiped the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "And he said, \u201CBlessed be the Lord God of my master Abraham,
        who has not forsaken His mercy and His truth toward my master. As for me,
        being on the way, the Lord  led me to the house of my master\u2019s brethren.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "So the young woman ran and told her mother\u2019s household these
        things."
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Now Rebekah had a brother whose name was  Laban, and Laban ran out
        to the man by the well. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "So it came to pass, when he saw the nose ring, and the bracelets
        on his sister\u2019s wrists, and when he heard the words of his sister Rebekah,
        saying, \u201CThus the man spoke to me,\u201D that he went to the man. And
        there he stood by the camels at the well. "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "And he said, \u201CCome in, O blessed of the Lord! Why do you stand
        outside? For I have prepared the house, and a place for the camels.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Then the man came to the house. And he unloaded the camels, and provided
        straw and feed for the camels, and water to wash his feet and the feet of
        the men who were with him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "Food was set before him to eat, but he said, \u201CI will not eat
        until I have told about my errand.\u201DAnd he said, \u201CSpeak on.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "So he said, \u201CI am Abraham\u2019s servant. "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'The Lord  has blessed my master greatly, and he has become great;
        and He has given him flocks and herds, silver and gold, male and female servants,
        and camels and donkeys. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "And Sarah my master\u2019s wife bore a son to my master when she
        was old; and to him he has given all that he has. "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "Now my master made me swear, saying, \u2018You shall not take a wife
        for my son from the daughters of the Canaanites, in whose land I dwell; "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "but you shall go to my father\u2019s house and to my family, and
        take a wife for my son.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "And I said to my master, \u2018Perhaps the woman will not follow
        me.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "But he said to me, \u2018The Lord, before whom I walk, will send
        His angel with you and prosper your way; and you shall take a wife for my
        son from my family and from my father\u2019s house. "
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "You will be clear from this oath when you arrive among my family;
        for if they will not give her to you, then you will be released from my oath.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "\u201CAnd this day I came to the well and said, \u2018O Lord God
        of my master Abraham, if You will now prosper the way in which I go, "
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: "behold, I stand by the well of water; and it shall come to pass that
        when the virgin comes out to draw water, and I say to her, \u201CPlease give
        me a little water from your pitcher to drink,\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: "and she says to me, \u201CDrink, and I will draw for your camels
        also,\u201D\u2014let her be the woman whom the Lord has appointed for my
        master\u2019s son.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: "\u201CBut before I had finished speaking in my heart, there was Rebekah,
        coming out with her pitcher on her shoulder; and she went down to the well
        and drew water. And I said to her, \u2018Please let me drink.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: "And she made haste and let her pitcher down from her shoulder, and
        said, \u2018Drink, and I will give your camels a drink also.\u2019 So I drank,
        and she gave the camels a drink also. "
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: "Then I asked her, and said, \u2018Whose daughter are you?\u2019 And
        she said, \u2018The daughter of Bethuel, Nahor\u2019s son, whom Milcah bore
        to him.\u2019 So I put the nose ring on her nose and the bracelets on her
        wrists. "
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: "And I bowed my head and worshiped the Lord, and blessed the Lord
        God of my master Abraham, who had led me in the way of truth to take the
        daughter of my master\u2019s brother for his son. "
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: "Now if you will deal kindly and truly with my master, tell me. And
        if not, tell me, that I may turn to the right hand or to the left.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: "Then Laban and Bethuel answered and said, \u201CThe thing comes from
        the Lord; we cannot speak to you either bad or good. "
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: "Here is Rebekah before you; take her and go, and let her be your
        master\u2019s son\u2019s wife, as the Lord has spoken.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: "And it came to pass, when Abraham\u2019s servant heard their words,
        that he worshiped the Lord, bowing  himself to the earth. "
      comments: []
    - name: '53: '
      title: 
      number: 53
      content: Then the servant brought out jewelry of silver, jewelry of gold, and
        clothing, and gave them to Rebekah. He also gave precious things to her brother
        and to her mother.
      comments: []
    - name: '54: '
      title: 
      number: 54
      content: "And he and the men who were with him ate and drank and stayed all
        night. Then they arose in the morning, and he said, \u201CSend me away to
        my master.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '55: '
      title: 
      number: 55
      content: "But her brother and her mother said, \u201CLet the young woman stay
        with us a  few days, at least ten; after that she may go.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '56: '
      title: 
      number: 56
      content: "And he said to them, \u201CDo not hinder me, since the Lord has prospered
        my way; send me away so that I may go to my master.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '57: '
      title: 
      number: 57
      content: "So they said, \u201CWe will call the young woman and ask her personally.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '58: '
      title: 
      number: 58
      content: "Then they called Rebekah and said to her, \u201CWill you go with
        this man?\u201DAnd she said, \u201CI will go.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '59: '
      title: 
      number: 59
      content: "So they sent away Rebekah their sister and her nurse, and Abraham\u2019s
        servant and his men. "
      comments: []
    - name: '60: '
      title: 
      number: 60
      content: "And they blessed Rebekah and said to her:\u201COur sister, may you
        becomeThe  mother  of thousands of ten thousands; And may your descendants
        possessThe gates of those who hate them.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '61: '
      title: 
      number: 61
      content: Then Rebekah and her maids arose, and they rode on the camels and
        followed the man. So the servant took Rebekah and departed.
      comments: []
    - name: '62: '
      title: 
      number: 62
      content: 'Now Isaac came from the way of Beer Lahai Roi, for he dwelt in the
        South. '
      comments: []
    - name: '63: '
      title: 
      number: 63
      content: 'And Isaac went out to meditate in the field in the evening; and he
        lifted his eyes and looked, and there, the camels were coming. '
      comments: []
    - name: '64: '
      title: 
      number: 64
      content: 'Then Rebekah lifted her eyes, and when she saw Isaac she dismounted
        from her camel; '
      comments: []
    - name: '65: '
      title: 
      number: 65
      content: "for she had said to the servant, \u201CWho is this man walking in
        the field to meet us?\u201DThe servant said, \u201CIt is my master.\u201D
        So she took a veil and covered herself."
      comments: []
    - name: '66: '
      title: 
      number: 66
      content: 'And the servant told Isaac all the things that he had done. '
      comments: []
    - name: '67: '
      title: 
      number: 67
      content: "Then Isaac brought her into his mother Sarah\u2019s tent; and he
        took Rebekah and she became his wife, and he loved her. So Isaac was comforted
        after his mother\u2019s death."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Abraham and Keturah'
      title: Abraham and Keturah
      number: 1
      content: 'Abraham again took a wife, and her name was  Keturah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And she bore him Zimran, Jokshan, Medan, Midian, Ishbak, and Shuah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Jokshan begot Sheba and Dedan. And the sons of Dedan were Asshurim,
        Letushim, and Leummim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: And the sons of Midian were Ephah, Epher, Hanoch, Abidah, and Eldaah.
        All these were the children of Keturah.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And Abraham gave all that he had to Isaac. '
      comments: []
    - name: "6: Abraham\u2019s Death and Burial"
      title: "Abraham\u2019s Death and Burial"
      number: 6
      content: But Abraham gave gifts to the sons of the concubines which Abraham
        had; and while he was still living he sent them eastward, away from Isaac
        his son, to the country of the east.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "This is the sum of the years of Abraham\u2019s life which he lived:
        one hundred and seventy-five years. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Then Abraham breathed his last and died in a good old age, an old
        man and full of  years, and was gathered to his people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And his sons Isaac and Ishmael buried him in the cave of Machpelah,
        which is before Mamre, in the field of Ephron the son of Zohar the Hittite, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'the field which Abraham purchased from the sons of Heth. There Abraham
        was buried, and Sarah his wife. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: The Families of Ishmael and Isaac'
      title: The Families of Ishmael and Isaac
      number: 11
      content: And it came to pass, after the death of Abraham, that God blessed
        his son Isaac. And Isaac dwelt at Beer Lahai Roi.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Now this is the genealogy of Ishmael, Abraham\u2019s son, whom Hagar
        the Egyptian, Sarah\u2019s maidservant, bore to Abraham. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And these were the names of the sons of Ishmael, by their names,
        according to their generations: The firstborn of Ishmael, Nebajoth; then
        Kedar, Adbeel, Mibsam, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Mishma, Dumah, Massa, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Hadar, Tema, Jetur, Naphish, and Kedemah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'These were the sons of Ishmael and these were their names, by their
        towns and their settlements, twelve princes according to their nations. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'These were the years of the life of Ishmael: one hundred and thirty-seven
        years; and he breathed his last and died, and was gathered to his people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: (They dwelt from Havilah as far as Shur, which is east of Egypt as
        you go toward Assyria.) He died in the presence of all his brethren.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "This is the genealogy of Isaac, Abraham\u2019s son. Abraham begot
        Isaac. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Isaac was forty years old when he took Rebekah as wife, the daughter
        of Bethuel the Syrian of Padan Aram, the sister of Laban the Syrian. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Now Isaac pleaded with the Lord for his wife, because she was barren;
        and the Lord granted his plea, and Rebekah his wife conceived. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "But the children struggled together within her; and she said, \u201CIf
        all  is well, why am  I  like this?\u201D So she went to inquire of the Lord."
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "And the Lord said to her:\u201CTwo nations are in your womb,Two peoples
        shall be separated from your body;One people shall be stronger than the other,And
        the older shall serve the younger.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'So when her days were fulfilled for  her to give birth, indeed there 
        were twins in her womb. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'And the first came out red. He  was  like a hairy garment all over;
        so they called his name Esau. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Afterward his brother came out, and his hand took hold of Esau\u2019s
        heel; so his name was called Jacob. Isaac was sixty years old when she bore
        them."
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'So the boys grew. And Esau was a skillful hunter, a man of the field;
        but Jacob was a mild man, dwelling in tents. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: Esau Sells His Birthright'
      title: Esau Sells His Birthright
      number: 28
      content: And Isaac loved Esau because he ate of  his game, but Rebekah loved
        Jacob.
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Now Jacob cooked a stew; and Esau came in from the field, and he
        was weary. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "And Esau said to Jacob, \u201CPlease feed me with that same red stew,
        for I am weary.\u201D Therefore his name was called Edom."
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "But Jacob said, \u201CSell me your birthright as of this day.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "And Esau said, \u201CLook, I am about to die; so what is this birthright
        to me?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "Then Jacob said, \u201CSwear to me as of this day.\u201DSo he swore
        to him, and sold his birthright to Jacob. "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: And Jacob gave Esau bread and stew of lentils; then he ate and drank,
        arose, and went his way. Thus Esau despised his birthright.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Isaac and Abimelech'
      title: Isaac and Abimelech
      number: 1
      content: There was a famine in the land, besides the first famine that was
        in the days of Abraham. And Isaac went to Abimelech king of the Philistines,
        in Gerar.
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Then the Lord appeared to him and said: \u201CDo not go down to Egypt;
        live in the land of which I shall tell you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Dwell in this land, and I will be with you and bless you; for to
        you and your descendants I give all these lands, and I will perform the oath
        which I swore to Abraham your father. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And I will make your descendants multiply as the stars of heaven;
        I will give to your descendants all these lands; and in your seed all the
        nations of the earth shall be blessed; '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "because Abraham obeyed My voice and kept My charge, My commandments,
        My statutes, and My laws.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'So Isaac dwelt in Gerar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And the men of the place asked about his wife. And he said, \u201CShe
        is my sister\u201D; for he was afraid to say, \u201CShe  is my wife,\u201D
        because  he  thought, \u201Clest the men of the place kill me for Rebekah,
        because she is  beautiful to behold.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Now it came to pass, when he had been there a long time, that Abimelech
        king of the Philistines looked through a window, and saw, and there was Isaac,
        showing endearment to Rebekah his wife. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then Abimelech called Isaac and said, \u201CQuite obviously she is
        your wife; so how could you say, \u2018She is my sister\u2019?\u201DIsaac
        said to him, \u201CBecause I said, \u2018Lest I die on account of her.\u2019
        \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And Abimelech said, \u201CWhat is this you have done to us? One of
        the people might soon have lain with your wife, and you would have brought
        guilt on us.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "So Abimelech charged all his people, saying, \u201CHe who touches
        this man or his wife shall surely be put to death.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Then Isaac sowed in that land, and reaped in the same year a hundredfold;
        and the Lord  blessed him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'The man began to prosper, and continued prospering until he became
        very prosperous; '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'for he had possessions of flocks and possessions of herds and a great
        number of servants. So the Philistines envied him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Now the Philistines had stopped up all the wells which his father\u2019s
        servants had dug in the days of Abraham his father, and they had filled them
        with earth. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And Abimelech said to Isaac, \u201CGo away from us, for you are much
        mightier than we.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Then Isaac departed from there and pitched his tent in the Valley
        of Gerar, and dwelt there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: And Isaac dug again the wells of water which they had dug in the days
        of Abraham his father, for the Philistines had stopped them up after the
        death of Abraham. He called them by the names which his father had called
        them.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Also Isaac\u2019s servants dug in the valley, and found a well of
        running water there. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "But the herdsmen of Gerar quarreled with Isaac\u2019s herdsmen, saying,
        \u201CThe water is ours.\u201D So he called the name of the well Esek, because
        they quarreled with him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Then they dug another well, and they quarreled over that one also.
        So he called its name Sitnah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "And he moved from there and dug another well, and they did not quarrel
        over it. So he called its name Rehoboth, because he said, \u201CFor now the
        Lord has made room for us, and we shall be fruitful in the land.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Then he went up from there to Beersheba. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "And the Lord  appeared to him the same night and said, \u201CI am
        the God of your father Abraham; do not fear, for I am with you. I will bless
        you and multiply your descendants for My servant Abraham\u2019s sake.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "So he built an altar there and called on the name of the Lord, and
        he pitched his tent there; and there Isaac\u2019s servants dug a well."
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Then Abimelech came to him from Gerar with Ahuzzath, one of his friends,
        and Phichol the commander of his army. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "And Isaac said to them, \u201CWhy have you come to me, since you
        hate me and have sent me away from you?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "But they said, \u201CWe have certainly seen that the Lord  is with
        you. So we said, \u2018Let there now be an oath between us, between you and
        us; and let us make a covenant with you, "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "that you will do us no harm, since we have not touched you, and since
        we have done nothing to you but good and have sent you away in peace. You
        are now the blessed of the Lord.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'So he made them a feast, and they ate and drank. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: Then they arose early in the morning and swore an oath with one another;
        and Isaac sent them away, and they departed from him in peace.
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "It came to pass the same day that Isaac\u2019s servants came and
        told him about the well which they had dug, and said to him, \u201CWe have
        found water.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: So he called it Shebah. Therefore the name of the city is Beersheba
        to this day.
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'When Esau was forty years old, he took as wives Judith the daughter
        of Beeri the Hittite, and Basemath the daughter of Elon the Hittite. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: And they were a grief of mind to Isaac and Rebekah.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Isaac Blesses Jacob'
      title: Isaac Blesses Jacob
      number: 1
      content: "Now it came to pass, when Isaac was old and his eyes were so dim
        that he could not see, that he called Esau his older son and said to him,
        \u201CMy son.\u201DAnd he answered him, \u201CHere I am.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Then he said, \u201CBehold now, I am old. I do not know the day of
        my death. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Now therefore, please take your weapons, your quiver and your bow,
        and go out to the field and hunt game for me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And make me savory food, such as I love, and bring it to me that
        I may eat, that my soul may bless you before I die.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Now Rebekah was listening when Isaac spoke to Esau his son. And Esau
        went to the field to hunt game and to bring it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "So Rebekah spoke to Jacob her son, saying, \u201CIndeed I heard your
        father speak to Esau your brother, saying, "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u2018Bring me game and make savory food for me, that I may eat it
        and bless you in the presence of the Lord before my death.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Now therefore, my son, obey my voice according to what I command
        you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Go now to the flock and bring me from there two choice kids of the
        goats, and I will make savory food from them for your father, such as he
        loves. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then you shall take it to your father, that he may eat it, and that
        he may bless you before his death.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And Jacob said to Rebekah his mother, \u201CLook, Esau my brother
        is a hairy man, and I am a smooth-skinned man. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Perhaps my father will feel me, and I shall seem to be a deceiver
        to him; and I shall bring a curse on myself and not a blessing.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "But his mother said to him, \u201CLet your curse be on me, my son;
        only obey my voice, and go, get them for me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And he went and got them and brought them to his mother, and his
        mother made savory food, such as his father loved. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Then Rebekah took the choice clothes of her elder son Esau, which
        were with her in the house, and put them on Jacob her younger son. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And she put the skins of the kids of the goats on his hands and on
        the smooth part of his neck. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: Then she gave the savory food and the bread, which she had prepared,
        into the hand of her son Jacob.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "So he went to his father and said, \u201CMy father.\u201DAnd he said,
        \u201CHere I am. Who are you, my son?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Jacob said to his father, \u201CI am Esau your firstborn; I have
        done just as you told me; please arise, sit and eat of my game, that your
        soul may bless me.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "But Isaac said to his son, \u201CHow is  it that you have found it
        so quickly, my son?\u201DAnd he said, \u201CBecause the Lord your God brought
        it to me.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Isaac said to Jacob, \u201CPlease come near, that I may feel you,
        my son, whether you are really my son Esau or not.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "So Jacob went near to Isaac his father, and he felt him and said,
        \u201CThe voice is Jacob\u2019s voice, but the hands are the hands of Esau.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "And he did not recognize him, because his hands were hairy like his
        brother Esau\u2019s hands; so he blessed him."
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Then he said, \u201CAre you really my son Esau?\u201DHe said, \u201CI
        am.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "He said, \u201CBring it near to me, and I will eat of my son\u2019s
        game, so that my soul may bless you.\u201D So he brought it near to him,
        and he ate; and he brought him wine, and he drank. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Then his father Isaac said to him, \u201CCome near now and kiss me,
        my son.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "And he came near and kissed him; and he smelled the smell of his
        clothing, and blessed him and said:\u201CSurely, the smell of my sonIs like
        the smell of a fieldWhich the Lord has blessed."
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: Therefore may God give youOf the dew of heaven,Of the fatness of the
        earth,And plenty of grain and wine.
      comments: []
    - name: "29: Esau\u2019s Lost Hope"
      title: "Esau\u2019s Lost Hope"
      number: 29
      content: "Let peoples serve you,And nations bow down to you.Be master over
        your brethren,And let your mother\u2019s sons bow down to you.Cursed be everyone
        who curses you,And blessed be those who bless you!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Now it happened, as soon as Isaac had finished blessing Jacob, and
        Jacob had scarcely gone out from the presence of Isaac his father, that Esau
        his brother came in from his hunting. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "He also had made savory food, and brought it to his father, and said
        to his father, \u201CLet my father arise and eat of his son\u2019s game,
        that your soul may bless me.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "And his father Isaac said to him, \u201CWho are you?\u201DSo he said,
        \u201CI am your son, your firstborn, Esau.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "Then Isaac trembled exceedingly, and said, \u201CWho? Where is the
        one who hunted game and brought it to me? I ate all of  it before you came,
        and I have blessed him\u2014and indeed he shall be blessed.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "When Esau heard the words of his father, he cried with an exceedingly
        great and bitter cry, and said to his father, \u201CBless me\u2014me also,
        O my father!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "But he said, \u201CYour brother came with deceit and has taken away
        your blessing.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "And Esau said, \u201CIs he not rightly named Jacob? For he has supplanted
        me these two times. He took away my birthright, and now look, he has taken
        away my blessing!\u201D And he said, \u201CHave you not reserved a blessing
        for me?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "Then Isaac answered and said to Esau, \u201CIndeed I have made him
        your master, and all his brethren I have given to him as servants; with grain
        and wine I have sustained him. What shall I do now for you, my son?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "And Esau said to his father, \u201CHave you only one blessing, my
        father? Bless me\u2014me also, O my father!\u201D And Esau lifted up his
        voice and wept."
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "Then Isaac his father answered and said to him:\u201CBehold, your
        dwelling shall be of the fatness of the earth,And of the dew of heaven from
        above."
      comments: []
    - name: '40: Jacob Escapes from Esau'
      title: Jacob Escapes from Esau
      number: 40
      content: "By your sword you shall live,And you shall serve your brother;And
        it shall come to pass, when you become restless,That you shall break his
        yoke from your neck.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "So Esau hated Jacob because of the blessing with which his father
        blessed him, and Esau said in his heart, \u201CThe days of mourning for my
        father are at hand; then I will kill my brother Jacob.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "And the words of Esau her older son were told to Rebekah. So she
        sent and called Jacob her younger son, and said to him, \u201CSurely your
        brother Esau comforts himself concerning you by  intending to kill you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'Now therefore, my son, obey my voice: arise, flee to my brother Laban
        in Haran. '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: "And stay with him a few days, until your brother\u2019s fury turns
        away, "
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: "until your brother\u2019s anger turns away from you, and he forgets
        what you have done to him; then I will send and bring you from there. Why
        should I be bereaved also of you both in one day?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: "And Rebekah said to Isaac, \u201CI am weary of my life because of
        the daughters of Heth; if Jacob takes a wife of the daughters of Heth, like
        these who  are the daughters of the land, what good will my life be to me?\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: "Then Isaac called Jacob and blessed him, and charged him, and said
        to him: \u201CYou shall not take a wife from the daughters of Canaan. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Arise, go to Padan Aram, to the house of Bethuel your mother\u2019s
        father; and take yourself a wife from there of the daughters of Laban your
        mother\u2019s brother."
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CMay God Almighty bless you,And make you fruitful and multiply
        you,That you may be an assembly of peoples;"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And give you the blessing of Abraham,To you and your descendants
        with you,That you may inherit the landIn which you are a stranger,Which God
        gave to Abraham.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: Esau Marries Mahalath'
      title: Esau Marries Mahalath
      number: 5
      content: So Isaac sent Jacob away, and he went to Padan Aram, to Laban the
        son of Bethuel the Syrian, the brother of Rebekah, the mother of Jacob and
        Esau.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Esau saw that Isaac had blessed Jacob and sent him away to Padan
        Aram to take himself a wife from there, and  that as he blessed him he gave
        him a charge, saying, \u201CYou shall not take a wife from the daughters
        of Canaan,\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'and that Jacob had obeyed his father and his mother and had gone
        to Padan Aram. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Also Esau saw that the daughters of Canaan did not please his father
        Isaac. '
      comments: []
    - name: "9: Jacob\u2019s Vow at Bethel"
      title: "Jacob\u2019s Vow at Bethel"
      number: 9
      content: "So Esau went to Ishmael and took Mahalath the daughter of Ishmael,
        Abraham\u2019s son, the sister of Nebajoth, to be his wife in addition to
        the wives he had."
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Now Jacob went out from Beersheba and went toward Haran. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'So he came to a certain place and stayed there all night, because
        the sun had set. And he took one of the stones of that place and put it at
        his head, and he lay down in that place to sleep. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: Then he dreamed, and behold, a ladder was set up on the earth, and
        its top reached to heaven; and there the angels of God were ascending and
        descending on it.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And behold, the Lord stood above it and said: \u201CI am the Lord
        God of Abraham your father and the God of Isaac; the land on which you lie
        I will give to you and your descendants. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Also your descendants shall be as the dust of the earth; you shall
        spread abroad to the west and the east, to the north and the south; and in
        you and in your seed all the families of the earth shall be blessed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Behold, I am with you and will keep you wherever you go, and will
        bring you back to this land; for I will not leave you until I have done what
        I have spoken to you.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Then Jacob awoke from his sleep and said, \u201CSurely the Lord is
        in this place, and I did not know it.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And he was afraid and said, \u201CHow awesome is this place! This
        is none other than the house of God, and this is the gate of heaven!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Then Jacob rose early in the morning, and took the stone that he
        had put at his head, set it up as a pillar, and poured oil on top of it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And he called the name of that place Bethel; but the name of that
        city had been Luz previously. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Then Jacob made a vow, saying, \u201CIf God will be with me, and
        keep me in this way that I am going, and give me bread to eat and clothing
        to put on, "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "so that I come back to my father\u2019s house in peace, then the
        Lord shall be my God. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "And this stone which I have set as a pillar shall be God\u2019s house,
        and of all that You give me I will surely give a tenth to You.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jacob Meets Rachel'
      title: Jacob Meets Rachel
      number: 1
      content: 'So Jacob went on his journey and came to the land of the people of
        the East. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And he looked, and saw a well in the field; and behold, there were
        three flocks of sheep lying by it; for out of that well they watered the
        flocks. A large stone was on the well\u2019s mouth. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Now all the flocks would be gathered there; and they would roll the
        stone from the well\u2019s mouth, water the sheep, and put the stone back
        in its place on the well\u2019s mouth."
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And Jacob said to them, \u201CMy brethren, where are you from?\u201DAnd
        they said, \u201CWe are from Haran.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then he said to them, \u201CDo you know Laban the son of Nahor?\u201DAnd
        they said, \u201CWe know him.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "So he said to them, \u201CIs he well?\u201DAnd they said, \u201CHe 
        is well. And look, his daughter Rachel is coming with the sheep.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Then he said, \u201CLook, it  is still high day; it  is not time
        for the cattle to be gathered together. Water the sheep, and go and feed
        them.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "But they said, \u201CWe cannot until all the flocks are gathered
        together, and they have rolled the stone from the well\u2019s mouth; then
        we water the sheep.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Now while he was still speaking with them, Rachel came with her father\u2019s
        sheep, for she was a shepherdess. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And it came to pass, when Jacob saw Rachel the daughter of Laban
        his mother\u2019s brother, and the sheep of Laban his mother\u2019s brother,
        that Jacob went near and rolled the stone from the well\u2019s mouth, and
        watered the flock of Laban his mother\u2019s brother. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Then Jacob kissed Rachel, and lifted up his voice and wept. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And Jacob told Rachel that he was  her father\u2019s relative and
        that he was Rebekah\u2019s son. So she ran and told her father."
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then it came to pass, when Laban heard the report about Jacob his
        sister\u2019s son, that he ran to meet him, and embraced him and kissed him,
        and brought him to his house. So he told Laban all these things. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: Jacob Marries Leah and Rachel'
      title: Jacob Marries Leah and Rachel
      number: 14
      content: "And Laban said to him, \u201CSurely you are my bone and my flesh.\u201D
        And he stayed with him for a month."
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Then Laban said to Jacob, \u201CBecause you are my relative, should
        you therefore serve me for nothing? Tell me, what should your wages be?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Now Laban had two daughters: the name of the elder was Leah, and
        the name of the younger was Rachel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Leah\u2019s eyes were delicate, but Rachel was beautiful of form
        and appearance."
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Now Jacob loved Rachel; so he said, \u201CI will serve you seven
        years for Rachel your younger daughter.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And Laban said, \u201CIt  is better that I give her to you than that
        I should give her to another man. Stay with me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: So Jacob served seven years for Rachel, and they seemed only a few
        days to him because of the love he had for her.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Then Jacob said to Laban, \u201CGive me my wife, for my days are
        fulfilled, that I may go in to her.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And Laban gathered together all the men of the place and made a feast. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Now it came to pass in the evening, that he took Leah his daughter
        and brought her to Jacob; and he went in to her. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And Laban gave his maid Zilpah to his daughter Leah as a maid. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "So it came to pass in the morning, that behold, it was Leah. And
        he said to Laban, \u201CWhat is this you have done to me? Was it not for
        Rachel that I served you? Why then have you deceived me?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "And Laban said, \u201CIt must not be done so in our country, to give
        the younger before the firstborn. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Fulfill her week, and we will give you this one also for the service
        which you will serve with me still another seven years.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Then Jacob did so and fulfilled her week. So he gave him his daughter
        Rachel as wife also. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'And Laban gave his maid Bilhah to his daughter Rachel as a maid. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: The Children of Jacob'
      title: The Children of Jacob
      number: 30
      content: Then Jacob also went in to Rachel, and he also loved Rachel more than
        Leah. And he served with Laban still another seven years.
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'When the Lord  saw that Leah was unloved, He opened her womb; but
        Rachel was barren. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "So Leah conceived and bore a son, and she called his name Reuben;
        for she said, \u201CThe Lord has surely looked on my affliction. Now therefore,
        my husband will love me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "Then she conceived again and bore a son, and said, \u201CBecause
        the Lord has heard that I am unloved, He has therefore given me this son
        also.\u201D And she called his name Simeon. "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "She conceived again and bore a son, and said, \u201CNow this time
        my husband will become attached to me, because I have borne him three sons.\u201D
        Therefore his name was called Levi. "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "And she conceived again and bore a son, and said, \u201CNow I will
        praise the Lord.\u201D Therefore she called his name Judah. Then she stopped
        bearing."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: "Now when Rachel saw that she bore Jacob no children, Rachel envied
        her sister, and said to Jacob, \u201CGive me children, or else I die!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And Jacob\u2019s anger was aroused against Rachel, and he said, \u201CAm
        I in the place of God, who has withheld from you the fruit of the womb?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "So she said, \u201CHere is my maid Bilhah; go in to her, and she
        will bear a  child on my knees, that I also may have children by her.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Then she gave him Bilhah her maid as wife, and Jacob went in to her. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And Bilhah conceived and bore Jacob a son. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then Rachel said, \u201CGod has judged my case; and He has also heard
        my voice and given me a son.\u201D Therefore she called his name Dan. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And Rachel\u2019s maid Bilhah conceived again and bore Jacob a second
        son. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then Rachel said, \u201CWith great wrestlings I have wrestled with
        my sister, and indeed I have prevailed.\u201D So she called his name Naphtali."
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'When Leah saw that she had stopped bearing, she took Zilpah her maid
        and gave her to Jacob as wife. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And Leah\u2019s maid Zilpah bore Jacob a son. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then Leah said, \u201CA troop comes!\u201D So she called his name
        Gad. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And Leah\u2019s maid Zilpah bore Jacob a second son. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then Leah said, \u201CI am happy, for the daughters will call me
        blessed.\u201D So she called his name Asher."
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Now Reuben went in the days of wheat harvest and found mandrakes
        in the field, and brought them to his mother Leah. Then Rachel said to Leah,
        \u201CPlease give me some of your son\u2019s mandrakes.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "But she said to her, \u201CIs  it a small matter that you have taken
        away my husband? Would you take away my son\u2019s mandrakes also?\u201DAnd
        Rachel said, \u201CTherefore he will lie with you tonight for your son\u2019s
        mandrakes.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "When Jacob came out of the field in the evening, Leah went out to
        meet him and said, \u201CYou must come in to me, for I have surely hired
        you with my son\u2019s mandrakes.\u201D And he lay with her that night."
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And God listened to Leah, and she conceived and bore Jacob a fifth
        son. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Leah said, \u201CGod has given me my wages, because I have given
        my maid to my husband.\u201D So she called his name Issachar. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Then Leah conceived again and bore Jacob a sixth son. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And Leah said, \u201CGod has endowed me with a good endowment; now
        my husband will dwell with me, because I have borne him six sons.\u201D So
        she called his name Zebulun. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: Afterward she bore a daughter, and called her name Dinah.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Then God remembered Rachel, and God listened to her and opened her
        womb. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "And she conceived and bore a son, and said, \u201CGod has taken away
        my reproach.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: "24: Jacob\u2019s Agreement with Laban"
      title: "Jacob\u2019s Agreement with Laban"
      number: 24
      content: "So she called his name Joseph, and said, \u201CThe Lord shall add
        to me another son.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "And it came to pass, when Rachel had borne Joseph, that Jacob said
        to Laban, \u201CSend me away, that I may go to my own place and to my country. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Give me my wives and my children for whom I have served you, and
        let me go; for you know my service which I have done for you.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "And Laban said to him, \u201CPlease stay, if I have found favor in
        your eyes, for I have learned by experience that the Lord has blessed me
        for your sake.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Then he said, \u201CName me your wages, and I will give it.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "So Jacob said to him, \u201CYou know how I have served you and how
        your livestock has been with me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "For what you had before I came  was little, and it has increased
        to a great amount; the Lord has blessed you since my coming. And now, when
        shall I also provide for my own house?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "So he said, \u201CWhat shall I give you?\u201DAnd Jacob said, \u201CYou
        shall not give me anything. If you will do this thing for me, I will again
        feed and keep your flocks: "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Let me pass through all your flock today, removing from there all
        the speckled and spotted sheep, and all the brown ones among the lambs, and
        the spotted and speckled among the goats; and these shall be my wages. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "So my righteousness will answer for me in time to come, when the
        subject of my wages comes before you: every one that is not speckled and
        spotted among the goats, and brown among the lambs, will be considered stolen,
        if it  is with me.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "And Laban said, \u201COh, that it were according to your word!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'So he removed that day the male goats that were speckled and spotted,
        all the female goats that were speckled and spotted, every one that had some
        white in it, and all the brown ones among the lambs, and gave them into the
        hand of his sons. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "Then he put three days\u2019 journey between himself and Jacob, and
        Jacob fed the rest of Laban\u2019s flocks."
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'Now Jacob took for himself rods of green poplar and of the almond
        and chestnut trees, peeled white strips in them, and exposed the white which
        was in the rods. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'And the rods which he had peeled, he set before the flocks in the
        gutters, in the watering troughs where the flocks came to drink, so that
        they should conceive when they came to drink. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'So the flocks conceived before the rods, and the flocks brought forth
        streaked, speckled, and spotted. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "Then Jacob separated the lambs, and made the flocks face toward the
        streaked and all the brown in the flock of Laban; but he put his own flocks
        by themselves and did not put them with Laban\u2019s flock."
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'And it came to pass, whenever the stronger livestock conceived, that
        Jacob placed the rods before the eyes of the livestock in the gutters, that
        they might conceive among the rods. '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "But when the flocks were feeble, he did not put them in; so the feebler
        were Laban\u2019s and the stronger Jacob\u2019s. "
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: Thus the man became exceedingly prosperous, and had large flocks,
        female and male servants, and camels and donkeys.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jacob Flees from Laban'
      title: Jacob Flees from Laban
      number: 1
      content: "Now Jacob heard the words of Laban\u2019s sons, saying, \u201CJacob
        has taken away all that was our father\u2019s, and from what was our father\u2019s
        he has acquired all this wealth.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And Jacob saw the countenance of Laban, and indeed it was not favorable
        toward him as before. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then the Lord said to Jacob, \u201CReturn to the land of your fathers
        and to your family, and I will be with you.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'So Jacob sent and called Rachel and Leah to the field, to his flock, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "and said to them, \u201CI see your father\u2019s countenance, that
        it is not favorable toward me as before; but the God of my father has been
        with me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And you know that with all my might I have served your father. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Yet your father has deceived me and changed my wages ten times, but
        God did not allow him to hurt me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "If he said thus: \u2018The speckled shall be your wages,\u2019 then
        all the flocks bore speckled. And if he said thus: \u2018The streaked shall
        be your wages,\u2019 then all the flocks bore streaked. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: So God has taken away the livestock of your father and given them
        to me.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CAnd it happened, at the time when the flocks conceived, that
        I lifted my eyes and saw in a dream, and behold, the rams which leaped upon
        the flocks were streaked, speckled, and gray-spotted. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then the Angel of God spoke to me in a dream, saying, \u2018Jacob.\u2019
        And I said, \u2018Here I am.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And He said, \u2018Lift your eyes now and see, all the rams which
        leap on the flocks are streaked, speckled, and gray-spotted; for I have seen
        all that Laban is doing to you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "I am the God of Bethel, where you anointed the pillar and where you
        made a vow to Me. Now arise, get out of this land, and return to the land
        of your family.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then Rachel and Leah answered and said to him, \u201CIs there still
        any portion or inheritance for us in our father\u2019s house? "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Are we not considered strangers by him? For he has sold us, and also
        completely consumed our money. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "For all these riches which God has taken from our father are really
        ours and our children\u2019s; now then, whatever God has said to you, do
        it.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Then Jacob rose and set his sons and his wives on camels. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And he carried away all his livestock and all his possessions which
        he had gained, his acquired livestock which he had gained in Padan Aram,
        to go to his father Isaac in the land of Canaan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Now Laban had gone to shear his sheep, and Rachel had stolen the
        household idols that were her father\u2019s. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And Jacob stole away, unknown to Laban the Syrian, in that he did
        not tell him that he intended to flee. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: Laban Pursues Jacob'
      title: Laban Pursues Jacob
      number: 21
      content: So he fled with all that he had. He arose and crossed the river, and
        headed toward the mountains of Gilead.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And Laban was told on the third day that Jacob had fled. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Then he took his brethren with him and pursued him for seven days\u2019
        journey, and he overtook him in the mountains of Gilead. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "But God had come to Laban the Syrian in a dream by night, and said
        to him, \u201CBe careful that you speak to Jacob neither good nor bad.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: So Laban overtook Jacob. Now Jacob had pitched his tent in the mountains,
        and Laban with his brethren pitched in the mountains of Gilead.
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "And Laban said to Jacob: \u201CWhat have you done, that you have
        stolen away unknown to me, and carried away my daughters like captives taken
        with the sword? "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Why did you flee away secretly, and steal away from me, and not tell
        me; for I might have sent you away with joy and songs, with timbrel and harp? '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'And you did not allow me to kiss my sons and my daughters. Now you
        have done foolishly in so doing. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "It is in my power to do you harm, but the God of your father spoke
        to me last night, saying, \u2018Be careful that you speak to Jacob neither
        good nor bad.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "And now you have surely gone because you greatly long for your father\u2019s
        house, but why did you steal my gods?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Then Jacob answered and said to Laban, \u201CBecause I was afraid,
        for I said, \u2018Perhaps you would take your daughters from me by force.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "With whomever you find your gods, do not let him live. In the presence
        of our brethren, identify what I have of yours and take it with you.\u201D
        For Jacob did not know that Rachel had stolen them."
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "And Laban went into Jacob\u2019s tent, into Leah\u2019s tent, and
        into the two maids\u2019 tents, but he did not find them. Then he went out
        of Leah\u2019s tent and entered Rachel\u2019s tent. "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "Now Rachel had taken the household idols, put them in the camel\u2019s
        saddle, and sat on them. And Laban searched all about the tent but did not
        find them.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "And she said to her father, \u201CLet it not displease my lord that
        I cannot rise before you, for the manner of women is with me.\u201D And he
        searched but did not find the household idols."
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "Then Jacob was angry and rebuked Laban, and Jacob answered and said
        to Laban: \u201CWhat is my trespass? What is my sin, that you have so hotly
        pursued me? "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'Although you have searched all my things, what part of your household
        things have you found? Set it here before my brethren and your brethren,
        that they may judge between us both! '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'These twenty years I have  been with you; your ewes and your female
        goats have not miscarried their young, and I have not eaten the rams of your
        flock. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'That which was torn by  beasts I did not bring to you; I bore the
        loss of it. You required it from my hand, whether stolen by day or stolen
        by night. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'There I was! In the day the drought consumed me, and the frost by
        night, and my sleep departed from my eyes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'Thus I have been in your house twenty years; I served you fourteen
        years for your two daughters, and six years for your flock, and you have
        changed my wages ten times. '
      comments: []
    - name: "42: Laban\u2019s Covenant with Jacob"
      title: "Laban\u2019s Covenant with Jacob"
      number: 42
      content: "Unless the God of my father, the God of Abraham and the Fear of Isaac,
        had been with me, surely now you would have sent me away empty-handed. God
        has seen my affliction and the labor of my hands, and rebuked you last night.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: "And Laban answered and said to Jacob, \u201CThese daughters are my
        daughters, and these children are my children, and this flock is my flock;
        all that you see is mine. But what can I do this day to these my daughters
        or to their children whom they have borne? "
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: "Now therefore, come, let us make a covenant, you and I, and let it
        be a witness between you and me.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'So Jacob took a stone and set it up as a pillar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: "Then Jacob said to his brethren, \u201CGather stones.\u201D And they
        took stones and made a heap, and they ate there on the heap. "
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: 'Laban called it Jegar Sahadutha, but Jacob called it Galeed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: "And Laban said, \u201CThis heap is a witness between you and me this
        day.\u201D Therefore its name was called Galeed, "
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: "also Mizpah, because he said, \u201CMay the Lord watch between you
        and me when we are absent one from another. "
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: "If you afflict my daughters, or if you take other wives besides my
        daughters, although no man is with us\u2014see, God is witness between you
        and me!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: "Then Laban said to Jacob, \u201CHere is this heap and here is this
        pillar, which I have placed between you and me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: 'This heap is a witness, and this pillar is a witness, that I will
        not pass beyond this heap to you, and you will not pass beyond this heap
        and this pillar to me, for harm. '
      comments: []
    - name: '53: '
      title: 
      number: 53
      content: "The God of Abraham, the God of Nahor, and the God of their father
        judge between us.\u201D And Jacob swore by the Fear of his father Isaac. "
      comments: []
    - name: '54: '
      title: 
      number: 54
      content: 'Then Jacob offered a sacrifice on the mountain, and called his brethren
        to eat bread. And they ate bread and stayed all night on the mountain. '
      comments: []
    - name: '55: '
      title: 
      number: 55
      content: And early in the morning Laban arose, and kissed his sons and daughters
        and blessed them. Then Laban departed and returned to his place.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Esau Comes to Meet Jacob'
      title: Esau Comes to Meet Jacob
      number: 1
      content: 'So Jacob went on his way, and the angels of God met him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "When Jacob saw them, he said, \u201CThis is God\u2019s camp.\u201D
        And he called the name of that place Mahanaim."
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Then Jacob sent messengers before him to Esau his brother in the
        land of Seir, the country of Edom. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And he commanded them, saying, \u201CSpeak thus to my lord Esau,
        \u2018Thus your servant Jacob says: \u201CI have dwelt with Laban and stayed
        there until now. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "I have oxen, donkeys, flocks, and male and female servants; and I
        have sent to tell my lord, that I may find favor in your sight.\u201D \u2019
        \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then the messengers returned to Jacob, saying, \u201CWe came to your
        brother Esau, and he also is coming to meet you, and four hundred men are
        with him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'So Jacob was greatly afraid and distressed; and he divided the people
        that were with him, and the flocks and herds and camels, into two companies. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And he said, \u201CIf Esau comes to the one company and attacks it,
        then the other company which is left will escape.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then Jacob said, \u201CO God of my father Abraham and God of my father
        Isaac, the Lord  who said to me, \u2018Return to your country and to your
        family, and I will deal well with you\u2019: "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'I am not worthy of the least of all the mercies and of all the truth
        which You have shown Your servant; for I crossed over this Jordan with my
        staff, and now I have become two companies. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Deliver me, I pray, from the hand of my brother, from the hand of
        Esau; for I fear him, lest he come and attack me and  the mother with the
        children. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "For You said, \u2018I will surely treat you well, and make your descendants
        as the sand of the sea, which cannot be numbered for multitude.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'So he lodged there that same night, and took what came to his hand
        as a present for Esau his brother: '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'two hundred female goats and twenty male goats, two hundred ewes
        and twenty rams, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'thirty milk camels with their colts, forty cows and ten bulls, twenty
        female donkeys and ten foals. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Then he delivered them to the hand of his servants, every drove by
        itself, and said to his servants, \u201CPass over before me, and put some
        distance between successive droves.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And he commanded the first one, saying, \u201CWhen Esau my brother
        meets you and asks you, saying, \u2018To whom do you belong, and where are
        you going? Whose are these in front of you?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "then you shall say, \u2018They are your servant Jacob\u2019s. It
        is a present sent to my lord Esau; and behold, he also is behind us.\u2019
        \u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "So he commanded the second, the third, and all who followed the droves,
        saying, \u201CIn this manner you shall speak to Esau when you find him; "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "and also say, \u2018Behold, your servant Jacob is behind us.\u2019
        \u201D For he said, \u201CI will appease him with the present that goes before
        me, and afterward I will see his face; perhaps he will accept me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: Wrestling with God'
      title: Wrestling with God
      number: 21
      content: So the present went on over before him, but he himself lodged that
        night in the camp.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And he arose that night and took his two wives, his two female servants,
        and his eleven sons, and crossed over the ford of Jabbok. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'He took them, sent them over the brook, and sent over what he had. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Then Jacob was left alone; and a Man wrestled with him until the
        breaking of day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Now when He saw that He did not prevail against him, He touched the
        socket of his hip; and the socket of Jacob\u2019s hip was out of joint as
        He wrestled with him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "And He said, \u201CLet Me go, for the day breaks.\u201DBut he said,
        \u201CI will not let You go unless You bless me!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "So He said to him, \u201CWhat is your name?\u201DHe said, \u201CJacob.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "And He said, \u201CYour name shall no longer be called Jacob, but
        Israel; for you have struggled with God and with men, and have prevailed.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Then Jacob asked, saying, \u201CTell me Your name, I pray.\u201DAnd
        He said, \u201CWhy is it that you ask about My name?\u201D And He blessed
        him there."
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "So Jacob called the name of the place Peniel: \u201CFor I have seen
        God face to face, and my life is preserved.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Just as he crossed over Penuel the sun rose on him, and he limped
        on his hip. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "Therefore to this day the children of Israel do not eat the muscle
        that shrank, which is on the hip socket, because He touched the socket of
        Jacob\u2019s hip in the muscle that shrank."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jacob and Esau Meet'
      title: Jacob and Esau Meet
      number: 1
      content: 'Now Jacob lifted his eyes and looked, and there, Esau was coming,
        and with him were four hundred men. So he divided the children among Leah,
        Rachel, and the two maidservants. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And he put the maidservants and their children in front, Leah and
        her children behind, and Rachel and Joseph last. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: Then he crossed over before them and bowed himself to the ground seven
        times, until he came near to his brother.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'But Esau ran to meet him, and embraced him, and fell on his neck
        and kissed him, and they wept. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And he lifted his eyes and saw the women and children, and said,
        \u201CWho are these with you?\u201DSo he said, \u201CThe children whom God
        has graciously given your servant.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Then the maidservants came near, they and their children, and bowed
        down. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: And Leah also came near with her children, and they bowed down. Afterward
        Joseph and Rachel came near, and they bowed down.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then Esau said, \u201CWhat do you mean  by  all this company which
        I met?\u201DAnd he said, \u201CThese  are  to find favor in the sight of
        my lord.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "But Esau said, \u201CI have enough, my brother; keep what you have
        for yourself.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And Jacob said, \u201CNo, please, if I have now found favor in your
        sight, then receive my present from my hand, inasmuch as I have seen your
        face as though I had seen the face of God, and you were pleased with me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Please, take my blessing that is brought to you, because God has
        dealt graciously with me, and because I have enough.\u201D So he urged him,
        and he took it."
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then Esau said, \u201CLet us take our journey; let us go, and I will
        go before you.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "But Jacob said to him, \u201CMy lord knows that the children are
        weak, and the flocks and herds which are nursing are with me. And if the
        men should drive them hard one day, all the flock will die. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Please let my lord go on ahead before his servant. I will lead on
        slowly at a pace which the livestock that go before me, and the children,
        are able to endure, until I come to my lord in Seir.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And Esau said, \u201CNow let me leave with you some of the people
        who are with me.\u201DBut he said, \u201CWhat need is there? Let me find
        favor in the sight of my lord.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'So Esau returned that day on his way to Seir. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: Jacob Comes to Canaan'
      title: Jacob Comes to Canaan
      number: 17
      content: And Jacob journeyed to Succoth, built himself a house, and made booths
        for his livestock. Therefore the name of the place is called Succoth.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Then Jacob came safely to the city of Shechem, which is in the land
        of Canaan, when he came from Padan Aram; and he pitched his tent before the
        city. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And he bought the parcel of land, where he had pitched his tent,
        from the children of Hamor, Shechem\u2019s father, for one hundred pieces
        of money. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: Then he erected an altar there and called it El Elohe Israel.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Dinah Incident'
      title: The Dinah Incident
      number: 1
      content: 'Now Dinah the daughter of Leah, whom she had borne to Jacob, went
        out to see the daughters of the land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And when Shechem the son of Hamor the Hivite, prince of the country,
        saw her, he took her and lay with her, and violated her. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'His soul was strongly attracted to Dinah the daughter of Jacob, and
        he loved the young woman and spoke kindly to the young woman. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "So Shechem spoke to his father Hamor, saying, \u201CGet me this young
        woman as a wife.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And Jacob heard that he had defiled Dinah his daughter. Now his sons
        were with his livestock in the field; so Jacob held his peace until they
        came. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Then Hamor the father of Shechem went out to Jacob to speak with
        him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And the sons of Jacob came in from the field when they heard it;
        and the men were grieved and very angry, because he had done a disgraceful
        thing in Israel by lying with Jacob\u2019s daughter, a thing which ought
        not to be done. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "But Hamor spoke with them, saying, \u201CThe soul of my son Shechem
        longs for your daughter. Please give her to him as a wife. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And make marriages with us; give your daughters to us, and take our
        daughters to yourselves. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "So you shall dwell with us, and the land shall be before you. Dwell
        and trade in it, and acquire possessions for yourselves in it.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then Shechem said to her father and her brothers, \u201CLet me find
        favor in your eyes, and whatever you say to me I will give. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Ask me ever so much dowry and gift, and I will give according to
        what you say to me; but give me the young woman as a wife.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'But the sons of Jacob answered Shechem and Hamor his father, and
        spoke deceitfully, because he had defiled Dinah their sister. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And they said to them, \u201CWe cannot do this thing, to give our
        sister to one who is uncircumcised, for that would  be a reproach to us. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'But on this condition we will consent to you: If you will become
        as we are, if every male of you is circumcised, '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'then we will give our daughters to you, and we will take your daughters
        to us; and we will dwell with you, and we will become one people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "But if you will not heed us and be circumcised, then we will take
        our daughter and be gone.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And their words pleased Hamor and Shechem, Hamor\u2019s son. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "So the young man did not delay to do the thing, because he delighted
        in Jacob\u2019s daughter. He was  more honorable than all the household of
        his father."
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And Hamor and Shechem his son came to the gate of their city, and
        spoke with the men of their city, saying: '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CThese men are at peace with us. Therefore let them dwell in
        the land and trade in it. For indeed the land is large enough for them. Let
        us take their daughters to us as wives, and let us give them our daughters. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Only on this condition will the men consent to dwell with us, to
        be one people: if every male among us is circumcised as they are circumcised. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Will not their livestock, their property, and every animal of theirs
        be ours? Only let us consent to them, and they will dwell with us.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: And all who went out of the gate of his city heeded Hamor and Shechem
        his son; every male was circumcised, all who went out of the gate of his
        city.
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Now it came to pass on the third day, when they were in pain, that
        two of the sons of Jacob, Simeon and Levi, Dinah\u2019s brothers, each took
        his sword and came boldly upon the city and killed all the males. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "And they killed Hamor and Shechem his son with the edge of the sword,
        and took Dinah from Shechem\u2019s house, and went out. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'The sons of Jacob came upon the slain, and plundered the city, because
        their sister had been defiled. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'They took their sheep, their oxen, and their donkeys, what was in
        the city and what was in the field, '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: and all their wealth. All their little ones and their wives they took
        captive; and they plundered even all that was in the houses.
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Then Jacob said to Simeon and Levi, \u201CYou have troubled me by
        making me obnoxious among the inhabitants of the land, among the Canaanites
        and the Perizzites; and since I am few in number, they will gather themselves
        together against me and kill me. I shall be destroyed, my household and I.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "But they said, \u201CShould he treat our sister like a harlot?\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Jacob\u2019s Return to Bethel"
      title: "Jacob\u2019s Return to Bethel"
      number: 1
      content: "Then God said to Jacob, \u201CArise, go up to Bethel and dwell there;
        and make an altar there to God, who appeared to you when you fled from the
        face of Esau your brother.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And Jacob said to his household and to all who were with him, \u201CPut
        away the foreign gods that are among you, purify yourselves, and change your
        garments. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then let us arise and go up to Bethel; and I will make an altar there
        to God, who answered me in the day of my distress and has been with me in
        the way which I have gone.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: So they gave Jacob all the foreign gods which were in their hands,
        and the earrings which were in their ears; and Jacob hid them under the terebinth
        tree which was by Shechem.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And they journeyed, and the terror of God was upon the cities that
        were all around them, and they did not pursue the sons of Jacob. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'So Jacob came to Luz (that is, Bethel), which is in the land of Canaan,
        he and all the people who were with him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: And he built an altar there and called the place El Bethel, because
        there God appeared to him when he fled from the face of his brother.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Now Deborah, Rebekah\u2019s nurse, died, and she was buried below
        Bethel under the terebinth tree. So the name of it was called Allon Bachuth."
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Then God appeared to Jacob again, when he came from Padan Aram, and
        blessed him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And God said to him, \u201CYour name is Jacob; your name shall not
        be called Jacob anymore, but Israel shall be your name.\u201D So He called
        his name Israel. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Also God said to him: \u201CI am God Almighty. Be fruitful and multiply;
        a nation and a company of nations shall proceed from you, and kings shall
        come from your body. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "The land which I gave Abraham and Isaac I give to you; and to your
        descendants after you I give this land.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Then God went up from him in the place where He talked with him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'So Jacob set up a pillar in the place where He talked with him, a
        pillar of stone; and he poured a drink offering on it, and he poured oil
        on it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: Death of Rachel'
      title: Death of Rachel
      number: 15
      content: And Jacob called the name of the place where God spoke with him, Bethel.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Then they journeyed from Bethel. And when there was but a little
        distance to go to Ephrath, Rachel labored in  childbirth, and she had hard
        labor. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Now it came to pass, when she was in hard labor, that the midwife
        said to her, \u201CDo not fear; you will have this son also.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And so it was, as her soul was departing (for she died), that she
        called his name Ben-Oni; but his father called him Benjamin. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'So Rachel died and was buried on the way to Ephrath (that is, Bethlehem). '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And Jacob set a pillar on her grave, which is the pillar of Rachel\u2019s
        grave to this day."
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Then Israel journeyed and pitched his tent beyond the tower of Eder. '
      comments: []
    - name: "22: Jacob\u2019s Twelve Sons"
      title: "Jacob\u2019s Twelve Sons"
      number: 22
      content: "And it happened, when Israel dwelt in that land, that Reuben went
        and lay with Bilhah his father\u2019s concubine; and Israel heard about 
        it.Now the sons of Jacob were twelve: "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "the sons of Leah were  Reuben, Jacob\u2019s firstborn, and Simeon,
        Levi, Judah, Issachar, and Zebulun; "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'the sons of Rachel were Joseph and Benjamin; '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "the sons of Bilhah, Rachel\u2019s maidservant, were Dan and Naphtali; "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: Death of Isaac'
      title: Death of Isaac
      number: 26
      content: "and the sons of Zilpah, Leah\u2019s maidservant, were Gad and Asher.
        These were the sons of Jacob who were born to him in Padan Aram."
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Then Jacob came to his father Isaac at Mamre, or Kirjath Arba (that
        is, Hebron), where Abraham and Isaac had dwelt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Now the days of Isaac were one hundred and eighty years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: So Isaac breathed his last and died, and was gathered to his people,
        being old and full of days. And his sons Esau and Jacob buried him.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Family of Esau'
      title: The Family of Esau
      number: 1
      content: 'Now this is the genealogy of Esau, who is Edom. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Esau took his wives from the daughters of Canaan: Adah the daughter
        of Elon the Hittite; Aholibamah the daughter of Anah, the daughter of Zibeon
        the Hivite; '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "and Basemath, Ishmael\u2019s daughter, sister of Nebajoth. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Now Adah bore Eliphaz to Esau, and Basemath bore Reuel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: And Aholibamah bore Jeush, Jaalam, and Korah. These were the sons
        of Esau who were born to him in the land of Canaan.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Then Esau took his wives, his sons, his daughters, and all the persons
        of his household, his cattle and all his animals, and all his goods which
        he had gained in the land of Canaan, and went to a country away from the
        presence of his brother Jacob. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'For their possessions were too great for them to dwell together,
        and the land where they were strangers could not support them because of
        their livestock. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: So Esau dwelt in Mount Seir. Esau is Edom.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And this is the genealogy of Esau the father of the Edomites in Mount
        Seir. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "These were the names of Esau\u2019s sons: Eliphaz the son of Adah
        the wife of Esau, and Reuel the son of Basemath the wife of Esau. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: And the sons of Eliphaz were Teman, Omar, Zepho, Gatam, and Kenaz.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Now Timna was the concubine of Eliphaz, Esau\u2019s son, and she
        bore Amalek to Eliphaz. These were the sons of Adah, Esau\u2019s wife."
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "These were the sons of Reuel: Nahath, Zerah, Shammah, and Mizzah.
        These were the sons of Basemath, Esau\u2019s wife."
      comments: []
    - name: '14: The Chiefs of Edom'
      title: The Chiefs of Edom
      number: 14
      content: "These were the sons of Aholibamah, Esau\u2019s wife, the daughter
        of Anah, the daughter of Zibeon. And she bore to Esau: Jeush, Jaalam, and
        Korah."
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'These were the chiefs of the sons of Esau. The sons of Eliphaz, the
        firstborn son of Esau, were Chief Teman, Chief Omar, Chief Zepho, Chief Kenaz, '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: Chief Korah, Chief Gatam, and Chief Amalek. These were the chiefs
        of Eliphaz in the land of Edom. They were the sons of Adah.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "These were the sons of Reuel, Esau\u2019s son: Chief Nahath, Chief
        Zerah, Chief Shammah, and Chief Mizzah. These were the chiefs of Reuel in
        the land of Edom. These were the sons of Basemath, Esau\u2019s wife."
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And these were the sons of Aholibamah, Esau\u2019s wife: Chief Jeush,
        Chief Jaalam, and Chief Korah. These were the chiefs who  descended from
        Aholibamah, Esau\u2019s wife, the daughter of Anah. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: The Sons of Seir'
      title: The Sons of Seir
      number: 19
      content: These were the sons of Esau, who is Edom, and these were their chiefs.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'These were the sons of Seir the Horite who inhabited the land: Lotan,
        Shobal, Zibeon, Anah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: Dishon, Ezer, and Dishan. These were the chiefs of the Horites, the
        sons of Seir, in the land of Edom.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "And the sons of Lotan were Hori and Hemam. Lotan\u2019s sister was
        Timna."
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'These were the sons of Shobal: Alvan, Manahath, Ebal, Shepho, and
        Onam.'
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'These were the sons of Zibeon: both Ajah and Anah. This was  the
        Anah who found the water in the wilderness as he pastured the donkeys of
        his father Zibeon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'These were the children of Anah: Dishon and Aholibamah the daughter
        of Anah.'
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'These were the sons of Dishon:Hemdan, Eshban, Ithran, and Cheran. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'These were the sons of Ezer: Bilhan, Zaavan, and Akan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'These were the sons of Dishan: Uz and Aran.'
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'These were the chiefs of the Horites: Chief Lotan, Chief Shobal,
        Chief Zibeon, Chief Anah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: The Kings of Edom'
      title: The Kings of Edom
      number: 30
      content: Chief Dishon, Chief Ezer, and Chief Dishan. These were the chiefs
        of the Horites, according to their chiefs in the land of Seir.
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Now these were the kings who reigned in the land of Edom before any
        king reigned over the children of Israel: '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Bela the son of Beor reigned in Edom, and the name of his city was
        Dinhabah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'And when Bela died, Jobab the son of Zerah of Bozrah reigned in his
        place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'When Jobab died, Husham of the land of the Temanites reigned in his
        place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'And when Husham died, Hadad the son of Bedad, who attacked Midian
        in the field of Moab, reigned in his place. And the name of his city was
        Avith. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'When Hadad died, Samlah of Masrekah reigned in his place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'And when Samlah died, Saul of Rehoboth-by-the-River reigned in his
        place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'When Saul died, Baal-Hanan the son of Achbor reigned in his place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: The Chiefs of Esau'
      title: The Chiefs of Esau
      number: 39
      content: "And when Baal-Hanan the son of Achbor died, Hadar reigned in his
        place; and the name of his city was Pau. His wife\u2019s name was Mehetabel,
        the daughter of Matred, the daughter of Mezahab."
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'And these were the names of the chiefs of Esau, according to their
        families and their places, by their names: Chief Timnah, Chief Alvah, Chief
        Jetheth, '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'Chief Aholibamah, Chief Elah, Chief Pinon, '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'Chief Kenaz, Chief Teman, Chief Mibzar, '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: Chief Magdiel, and Chief Iram. These were the chiefs of Edom, according
        to their dwelling places in the land of their possession. Esau was the father
        of the Edomites.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Joseph Dreams of Greatness'
      title: Joseph Dreams of Greatness
      number: 1
      content: 'Now Jacob dwelt in the land where his father was a stranger, in the
        land of Canaan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "This is the history of Jacob.Joseph, being seventeen years old, was
        feeding the flock with his brothers. And the lad was with the sons of Bilhah
        and the sons of Zilpah, his father\u2019s wives; and Joseph brought a bad
        report of them to his father."
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Now Israel loved Joseph more than all his children, because he was 
        the son of his old age. Also he made him a tunic of many colors. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: But when his brothers saw that their father loved him more than all
        his brothers, they hated him and could not speak peaceably to him.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Now Joseph had a dream, and he told it to his brothers; and they
        hated him even more. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "So he said to them, \u201CPlease hear this dream which I have dreamed: "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "There we were, binding sheaves in the field. Then behold, my sheaf
        arose and also stood upright; and indeed your sheaves stood all around and
        bowed down to my sheaf.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And his brothers said to him, \u201CShall you indeed reign over us?
        Or shall you indeed have dominion over us?\u201D So they hated him even more
        for his dreams and for his words."
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then he dreamed still another dream and told it to his brothers,
        and said, \u201CLook, I have dreamed another dream. And this time, the sun,
        the moon, and the eleven stars bowed down to me.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "So he told it to his father and his brothers; and his father rebuked
        him and said to him, \u201CWhat is this dream that you have dreamed? Shall
        your mother and I and your brothers indeed come to bow down to the earth
        before you?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: Joseph Sold by His Brothers'
      title: Joseph Sold by His Brothers
      number: 11
      content: And his brothers envied him, but his father kept the matter in  mind.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then his brothers went to feed their father\u2019s flock in Shechem. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And Israel said to Joseph, \u201CAre not your brothers feeding the 
        flock in Shechem? Come, I will send you to them.\u201DSo he said to him,
        \u201CHere I am.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then he said to him, \u201CPlease go and see if it is well with your
        brothers and well with the flocks, and bring back word to me.\u201D So he
        sent him out of the Valley of Hebron, and he went to Shechem."
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Now a certain man found him, and there he was, wandering in the field.
        And the man asked him, saying, \u201CWhat are you seeking?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "So he said, \u201CI am seeking my brothers. Please tell me where
        they are feeding their  flocks.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And the man said, \u201CThey have departed from here, for I heard
        them say, \u2018Let us go to Dothan.\u2019 \u201D So Joseph went after his
        brothers and found them in Dothan."
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Now when they saw him afar off, even before he came near them, they
        conspired against him to kill him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Then they said to one another, \u201CLook, this dreamer is coming! "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Come therefore, let us now kill him and cast him into some pit; and
        we shall say, \u2018Some wild beast has devoured him.\u2019 We shall see
        what will become of his dreams!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "But Reuben heard it, and he delivered him out of their hands, and
        said, \u201CLet us not kill him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "And Reuben said to them, \u201CShed no blood, but cast him into this
        pit which is in the wilderness, and do not lay a hand on him\u201D\u2014that
        he might deliver him out of their hands, and bring him back to his father."
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'So it came to pass, when Joseph had come to his brothers, that they
        stripped Joseph of his tunic, the tunic of many colors that was on him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: Then they took him and cast him into a pit. And the pit was empty;
        there  was no water in it.
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'And they sat down to eat a meal. Then they lifted their eyes and
        looked, and there was a company of Ishmaelites, coming from Gilead with their
        camels, bearing spices, balm, and myrrh, on their way to carry them down
        to Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "So Judah said to his brothers, \u201CWhat profit is  there if we
        kill our brother and conceal his blood? "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Come and let us sell him to the Ishmaelites, and let not our hand
        be upon him, for he is  our brother and  our flesh.\u201D And his brothers
        listened. "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: Then Midianite traders passed by; so the  brothers pulled Joseph up
        and lifted him out of the pit, and sold him to the Ishmaelites for twenty
        shekels of silver. And they took Joseph to Egypt.
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Then Reuben returned to the pit, and indeed Joseph was not in the
        pit; and he tore his clothes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "And he returned to his brothers and said, \u201CThe lad is no more;
        and I, where shall I go?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "So they took Joseph\u2019s tunic, killed a kid of the goats, and
        dipped the tunic in the blood. "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "Then they sent the tunic of many colors, and they brought it to their
        father and said, \u201CWe have found this. Do you know whether it is your
        son\u2019s tunic or not?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "And he recognized it and said, \u201CIt  is my son\u2019s tunic.
        A wild beast has devoured him. Without doubt Joseph is torn to pieces.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Then Jacob tore his clothes, put sackcloth on his waist, and mourned
        for his son many days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "And all his sons and all his daughters arose to comfort him; but
        he refused to be comforted, and he said, \u201CFor I shall go down into the
        grave to my son in mourning.\u201D Thus his father wept for him."
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: Now the Midianites had sold him in Egypt to Potiphar, an officer of
        Pharaoh and captain of the guard.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Judah and Tamar'
      title: Judah and Tamar
      number: 1
      content: 'It came to pass at that time that Judah departed from his brothers,
        and visited a certain Adullamite whose name was Hirah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And Judah saw there a daughter of a certain Canaanite whose name
        was  Shua, and he married her and went in to her. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'So she conceived and bore a son, and he called his name Er. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'She conceived again and bore a son, and she called his name Onan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: And she conceived yet again and bore a son, and called his name Shelah.
        He was at Chezib when she bore him.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Then Judah took a wife for Er his firstborn, and her name was  Tamar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "But Er, Judah\u2019s firstborn, was wicked in the sight of the Lord,
        and the Lord killed him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And Judah said to Onan, \u201CGo in to your brother\u2019s wife and
        marry her, and raise up an heir to your brother.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "But Onan knew that the heir would not be his; and it came to pass,
        when he went in to his brother\u2019s wife, that he emitted on the ground,
        lest he should give an heir to his brother. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: And the thing which he did displeased the Lord; therefore He killed
        him also.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then Judah said to Tamar his daughter-in-law, \u201CRemain a widow
        in your father\u2019s house till my son Shelah is grown.\u201D For he said,
        \u201CLest he also die like his brothers.\u201D And Tamar went and dwelt
        in her father\u2019s house."
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Now in the process of time the daughter of Shua, Judah\u2019s wife,
        died; and Judah was comforted, and went up to his sheepshearers at Timnah,
        he and his friend Hirah the Adullamite. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And it was told Tamar, saying, \u201CLook, your father-in-law is
        going up to Timnah to shear his sheep.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "So she took off her widow\u2019s garments, covered herself with a
        veil and wrapped herself, and sat in an open place which was on the way to
        Timnah; for she saw that Shelah was grown, and she was not given to him as
        a wife. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'When Judah saw her, he thought she was a harlot, because she had
        covered her face. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Then he turned to her by the way, and said, \u201CPlease let me come
        in to you\u201D; for he did not know that she was his daughter-in-law.So
        she said, \u201CWhat will you give me, that you may come in to me?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And he said, \u201CI will send a young goat from the flock.\u201DSo
        she said, \u201CWill you give me a pledge till you send it?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Then he said, \u201CWhat pledge shall I give you?\u201DSo she said,
        \u201CYour signet and cord, and your staff that is in your hand.\u201D Then
        he gave them to her, and went in to her, and she conceived by him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: So she arose and went away, and laid aside her veil and put on the
        garments of her widowhood.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And Judah sent the young goat by the hand of his friend the Adullamite,
        to receive his pledge from the woman\u2019s hand, but he did not find her. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Then he asked the men of that place, saying, \u201CWhere is the harlot
        who was openly by the roadside?\u201DAnd they said, \u201CThere was no harlot
        in this place.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "So he returned to Judah and said, \u201CI cannot find her. Also,
        the men of the place said there was no harlot in this place.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Then Judah said, \u201CLet her take them for herself, lest we be
        shamed; for I sent this young goat and you have not found her.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "And it came to pass, about three months after, that Judah was told,
        saying, \u201CTamar your daughter-in-law has played the harlot; furthermore
        she is with child by harlotry.\u201DSo Judah said, \u201CBring her out and
        let her be burned!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "When she was brought out, she sent to her father-in-law, saying,
        \u201CBy the man to whom these belong, I am with child.\u201D And she said,
        \u201CPlease determine whose these are\u2014the signet and cord, and staff.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "So Judah acknowledged them and said, \u201CShe has been more righteous
        than I, because I did not give her to Shelah my son.\u201D And he never knew
        her again."
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Now it came to pass, at the time for giving birth, that behold, twins
        were in her womb. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "And so it was, when she was giving birth, that the  one put out his
        hand; and the midwife took a scarlet thread and bound it on his hand, saying,
        \u201CThis one came out first.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Then it happened, as he drew back his hand, that his brother came
        out unexpectedly; and she said, \u201CHow did you break through? This breach
        be upon you!\u201D Therefore his name was called Perez. "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: Afterward his brother came out who had the scarlet thread on his hand.
        And his name was called Zerah.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Joseph a Slave in Egypt'
      title: Joseph a Slave in Egypt
      number: 1
      content: 'Now Joseph had been taken down to Egypt. And Potiphar, an officer
        of Pharaoh, captain of the guard, an Egyptian, bought him from the Ishmaelites
        who had taken him down there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'The Lord was with Joseph, and he was a successful man; and he was
        in the house of his master the Egyptian. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And his master saw that the Lord  was with him and that the Lord 
        made all he did to prosper in his hand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'So Joseph found favor in his sight, and served him. Then he made
        him overseer of his house, and all that he had he put under his authority. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "So it was, from the time that he had made him overseer of his house
        and all that he had, that the Lord blessed the Egyptian\u2019s house for
        Joseph\u2019s sake; and the blessing of the Lord was on all that he had in
        the house and in the field. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Thus he left all that he had in Joseph\u2019s hand, and he did not
        know what he had except for the bread which he ate.Now Joseph was handsome
        in form and appearance."
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And it came to pass after these things that his master\u2019s wife
        cast longing eyes on Joseph, and she said, \u201CLie with me.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "But he refused and said to his master\u2019s wife, \u201CLook, my
        master does not know what is with me in the house, and he has committed all
        that he has to my hand. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "There  is no one greater in this house than I, nor has he kept back
        anything from me but you, because you are his wife. How then can I do this
        great wickedness, and sin against God?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: So it was, as she spoke to Joseph day by day, that he did not heed
        her, to lie with her or to be with her.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'But it happened about this time, when Joseph went into the house
        to do his work, and none of the men of the house was inside, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "that she caught him by his garment, saying, \u201CLie with me.\u201D
        But he left his garment in her hand, and fled and ran outside. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And so it was, when she saw that he had left his garment in her hand
        and fled outside, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "that she called to the men of her house and spoke to them, saying,
        \u201CSee, he has brought in to us a Hebrew to mock us. He came in to me
        to lie with me, and I cried out with a loud voice. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And it happened, when he heard that I lifted my voice and cried out,
        that he left his garment with me, and fled and went outside.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'So she kept his garment with her until his master came home. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Then she spoke to him with words like these, saying, \u201CThe Hebrew
        servant whom you brought to us came in to me to mock me; "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "so it happened, as I lifted my voice and cried out, that he left
        his garment with me and fled outside.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "So it was, when his master heard the words which his wife spoke to
        him, saying, \u201CYour servant did to me after this manner,\u201D that his
        anger was aroused. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Then Joseph\u2019s master took him and put him into the prison, a
        place where the king\u2019s prisoners were confined. And he was there in
        the prison. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'But the Lord was with Joseph and showed him mercy, and He gave him
        favor in the sight of the keeper of the prison. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "And the keeper of the prison committed to Joseph\u2019s hand all
        the prisoners who were in the prison; whatever they did there, it was his
        doing. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "The keeper of the prison did not look into anything that  was under
        Joseph\u2019s authority, because the Lord was with him; and whatever he did,
        the Lord made it prosper."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: The Prisoners\u2019 Dreams"
      title: "The Prisoners\u2019 Dreams"
      number: 1
      content: 'It came to pass after these things that the butler and the baker
        of the king of Egypt offended their lord, the king of Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And Pharaoh was angry with his two officers, the chief butler and
        the chief baker. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'So he put them in custody in the house of the captain of the guard,
        in the prison, the place where Joseph was confined. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: And the captain of the guard charged Joseph with them, and he served
        them; so they were in custody for a while.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then the butler and the baker of the king of Egypt, who were confined
        in the prison, had a dream, both of them, each man\u2019s dream in one night
        and each man\u2019s dream with its own interpretation. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And Joseph came in to them in the morning and looked at them, and
        saw that they were sad. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "So he asked Pharaoh\u2019s officers who were with him in the custody
        of his lord\u2019s house, saying, \u201CWhy do you look so sad today?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And they said to him, \u201CWe each have had a dream, and there 
        is no interpreter of it.\u201DSo Joseph said to them, \u201CDo not interpretations
        belong to God? Tell them to me, please.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then the chief butler told his dream to Joseph, and said to him,
        \u201CBehold, in my dream a vine was before me, "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'and in the vine were three branches; it was as though it budded,
        its blossoms shot forth, and its clusters brought forth ripe grapes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then Pharaoh\u2019s cup was in my hand; and I took the grapes and
        pressed them into Pharaoh\u2019s cup, and placed the cup in Pharaoh\u2019s
        hand.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And Joseph said to him, \u201CThis is the interpretation of it: The
        three branches are three days. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Now within three days Pharaoh will lift up your head and restore
        you to your place, and you will put Pharaoh\u2019s cup in his hand according
        to the former manner, when you were his butler. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'But remember me when it is well with you, and please show kindness
        to me; make mention of me to Pharaoh, and get me out of this house. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "For indeed I was stolen away from the land of the Hebrews; and also
        I have done nothing here that they should put me into the dungeon.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "When the chief baker saw that the interpretation was good, he said
        to Joseph, \u201CI also was in my dream, and there were three white baskets
        on my head. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "In the uppermost basket were all kinds of baked goods for Pharaoh,
        and the birds ate them out of the basket on my head.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "So Joseph answered and said, \u201CThis is the interpretation of
        it: The three baskets are three days. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Within three days Pharaoh will lift off your head from you and hang
        you on a tree; and the birds will eat your flesh from you.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Now it came to pass on the third day, which  was Pharaoh\u2019s birthday,
        that he made a feast for all his servants; and he lifted up the head of the
        chief butler and of the chief baker among his servants. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Then he restored the chief butler to his butlership again, and he
        placed the cup in Pharaoh\u2019s hand. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'But he hanged the chief baker, as Joseph had interpreted to them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: Yet the chief butler did not remember Joseph, but forgot him.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Pharaoh\u2019s Dreams"
      title: "Pharaoh\u2019s Dreams"
      number: 1
      content: 'Then it came to pass, at the end of two full years, that Pharaoh
        had a dream; and behold, he stood by the river. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Suddenly there came up out of the river seven cows, fine looking
        and fat; and they fed in the meadow. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Then behold, seven other cows came up after them out of the river,
        ugly and gaunt, and stood by the other cows on the bank of the river. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And the ugly and gaunt cows ate up the seven fine looking and fat
        cows. So Pharaoh awoke. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'He slept and dreamed a second time; and suddenly seven heads of grain
        came up on one stalk, plump and good. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Then behold, seven thin heads, blighted by the east wind, sprang
        up after them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And the seven thin heads devoured the seven plump and full heads.
        So Pharaoh awoke, and indeed, it  was a dream. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: Now it came to pass in the morning that his spirit was troubled, and
        he sent and called for all the magicians of Egypt and all its wise men. And
        Pharaoh told them his dreams, but there  was no one who could interpret them
        for Pharaoh.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then the chief butler spoke to Pharaoh, saying: \u201CI remember
        my faults this day. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'When Pharaoh was angry with his servants, and put me in custody in
        the house of the captain of the guard, both me and the chief baker, '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'we each had a dream in one night, he and I. Each of us dreamed according
        to the interpretation of his own dream. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Now there was a young Hebrew man with us there, a servant of the
        captain of the guard. And we told him, and he interpreted our dreams for
        us; to each man he interpreted according to his own dream. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And it came to pass, just as he interpreted for us, so it happened.
        He restored me to my office, and he hanged him.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Then Pharaoh sent and called Joseph, and they brought him quickly
        out of the dungeon; and he shaved, changed his clothing, and came to Pharaoh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And Pharaoh said to Joseph, \u201CI have had a dream, and there 
        is no one who can interpret it. But I have heard it said of you that you
        can understand a dream, to interpret it.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "So Joseph answered Pharaoh, saying, \u201CIt  is not in me; God will
        give Pharaoh an answer of peace.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Then Pharaoh said to Joseph: \u201CBehold, in my dream I stood on
        the bank of the river. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Suddenly seven cows came up out of the river, fine looking and fat;
        and they fed in the meadow. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Then behold, seven other cows came up after them, poor and very ugly
        and gaunt, such ugliness as I have never seen in all the land of Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And the gaunt and ugly cows ate up the first seven, the fat cows. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'When they had eaten them up, no one would have known that they had
        eaten them, for they were just as ugly as at the beginning. So I awoke. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Also I saw in my dream, and suddenly seven heads came up on one stalk,
        full and good. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Then behold, seven heads, withered, thin, and blighted by the east
        wind, sprang up after them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "And the thin heads devoured the seven good heads. So I told this
        to the magicians, but there  was no one who could explain it to me.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Then Joseph said to Pharaoh, \u201CThe dreams of Pharaoh are one;
        God has shown Pharaoh what He is about to do: "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'The seven good cows are seven years, and the seven good heads are
        seven years; the dreams are one. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'And the seven thin and ugly cows which came up after them are seven
        years, and the seven empty heads blighted by the east wind are seven years
        of famine. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'This is the thing which I have spoken to Pharaoh. God has shown Pharaoh
        what He is about to do. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Indeed seven years of great plenty will come throughout all the land
        of Egypt; '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'but after them seven years of famine will arise, and all the plenty
        will be forgotten in the land of Egypt; and the famine will deplete the land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'So the plenty will not be known in the land because of the famine
        following, for it will  be very severe. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: And the dream was repeated to Pharaoh twice because the thing is established
        by God, and God will shortly bring it to pass.
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "\u201CNow therefore, let Pharaoh select a discerning and wise man,
        and set him over the land of Egypt. "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Let Pharaoh do this, and let him appoint officers over the land,
        to collect one-fifth of  the  produce of the land of Egypt in the seven plentiful
        years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'And let them gather all the food of those good years that are coming,
        and store up grain under the authority of Pharaoh, and let them keep food
        in the cities. '
      comments: []
    - name: "36: Joseph\u2019s Rise to Power"
      title: "Joseph\u2019s Rise to Power"
      number: 36
      content: "Then that food shall be as a reserve for the land for the seven years
        of famine which shall be in the land of Egypt, that the land may not perish
        during the famine.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'So the advice was good in the eyes of Pharaoh and in the eyes of
        all his servants. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "And Pharaoh said to his servants, \u201CCan we find such  a  one
        as this, a man in whom is the Spirit of God?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "Then Pharaoh said to Joseph, \u201CInasmuch as God has shown you
        all this, there  is no one as discerning and wise as you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "You shall be over my house, and all my people shall be ruled according
        to your word; only in regard to the throne will I be greater than you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "And Pharaoh said to Joseph, \u201CSee, I have set you over all the
        land of Egypt.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "Then Pharaoh took his signet ring off his hand and put it on Joseph\u2019s
        hand; and he clothed him in garments of fine linen and put a gold chain around
        his neck. "
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: "And he had him ride in the second chariot which he had; and they
        cried out before him, \u201CBow the knee!\u201D So he set him over all the
        land of Egypt. "
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: "Pharaoh also said to Joseph, \u201CI am Pharaoh, and without your
        consent no man may lift his hand or foot in all the land of Egypt.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: "And Pharaoh called Joseph\u2019s name Zaphnath-Paaneah. And he gave
        him as a wife Asenath, the daughter of Poti-Pherah priest of On. So Joseph
        went out over all the land of Egypt."
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'Joseph was thirty years old when he stood before Pharaoh king of
        Egypt. And Joseph went out from the presence of Pharaoh, and went throughout
        all the land of Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: 'Now in the seven plentiful years the ground brought forth abundantly. '
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: 'So he gathered up all the food of the seven years which were in the
        land of Egypt, and laid up the food in the cities; he laid up in every city
        the food of the fields which surrounded them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: Joseph gathered very much grain, as the sand of the sea, until he
        stopped counting, for it  was immeasurable.
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: 'And to Joseph were born two sons before the years of famine came,
        whom Asenath, the daughter of Poti-Pherah priest of On, bore to him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: "Joseph called the name of the firstborn Manasseh: \u201CFor God has
        made me forget all my toil and all my father\u2019s house.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: "And the name of the second he called Ephraim: \u201CFor God has caused
        me to be fruitful in the land of my affliction.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '53: '
      title: 
      number: 53
      content: 'Then the seven years of plenty which were in the land of Egypt ended, '
      comments: []
    - name: '54: '
      title: 
      number: 54
      content: 'and the seven years of famine began to come, as Joseph had said.
        The famine was in all lands, but in all the land of Egypt there was bread. '
      comments: []
    - name: '55: '
      title: 
      number: 55
      content: "So when all the land of Egypt was famished, the people cried to Pharaoh
        for bread. Then Pharaoh said to all the Egyptians, \u201CGo to Joseph; whatever
        he says to you, do.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '56: '
      title: 
      number: 56
      content: 'The famine was over all the face of the earth, and Joseph opened
        all the storehouses and sold to the Egyptians. And the famine became severe
        in the land of Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '57: '
      title: 
      number: 57
      content: So all countries came to Joseph in Egypt to buy grain, because the
        famine was severe in all lands.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Joseph\u2019s Brothers Go to Egypt"
      title: "Joseph\u2019s Brothers Go to Egypt"
      number: 1
      content: "When Jacob saw that there was grain in Egypt, Jacob said to his sons,
        \u201CWhy do you look at one another?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And he said, \u201CIndeed I have heard that there is grain in Egypt;
        go down to that place and buy for us there, that we may live and not die.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "So Joseph\u2019s ten brothers went down to buy grain in Egypt. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "But Jacob did not send Joseph\u2019s brother Benjamin with his brothers,
        for he said, \u201CLest some calamity befall him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: And the sons of Israel went to buy grain among those who journeyed,
        for the famine was in the land of Canaan.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Now Joseph was governor over the land; and it was he who sold to
        all the people of the land. And Joseph\u2019s brothers came and bowed down
        before him with their faces to the earth. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Joseph saw his brothers and recognized them, but he acted as a stranger
        to them and spoke roughly to them. Then he said to them, \u201CWhere do you
        come from?\u201DAnd they said, \u201CFrom the land of Canaan to buy food.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'So Joseph recognized his brothers, but they did not recognize him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then Joseph remembered the dreams which he had dreamed about them,
        and said to them, \u201CYou are spies! You have come to see the nakedness
        of the land!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And they said to him, \u201CNo, my lord, but your servants have come
        to buy food. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "We are all one man\u2019s sons; we are honest men; your servants
        are not spies.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "But he said to them, \u201CNo, but you have come to see the nakedness
        of the land.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And they said, \u201CYour servants are twelve brothers, the sons
        of one man in the land of Canaan; and in fact, the youngest is with our father
        today, and one is no more.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "But Joseph said to them, \u201CIt is as I spoke to you, saying, \u2018You
        are spies!\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'In this manner you shall be tested: By the life of Pharaoh, you shall
        not leave this place unless your youngest brother comes here. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Send one of you, and let him bring your brother; and you shall be
        kept in prison, that your words may be tested to see whether there  is any
        truth in you; or else, by the life of Pharaoh, surely you are spies!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: So he put them all together in prison three days.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Then Joseph said to them the third day, \u201CDo this and live, for
        I fear God: "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'If you are honest men, let one of your brothers be confined to your
        prison house; but you, go and carry grain for the famine of your houses. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And bring your youngest brother to me; so your words will be verified,
        and you shall not die.\u201DAnd they did so. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Then they said to one another, \u201CWe are truly guilty concerning
        our brother, for we saw the anguish of his soul when he pleaded with us,
        and we would not hear; therefore this distress has come upon us.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "And Reuben answered them, saying, \u201CDid I not speak to you, saying,
        \u2018Do not sin against the boy\u2019; and you would not listen? Therefore
        behold, his blood is now required of us.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'But they did not know that Joseph understood them, for he spoke to
        them through an interpreter. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: The Brothers Return to Canaan'
      title: The Brothers Return to Canaan
      number: 24
      content: And he turned himself away from them and wept. Then he returned to
        them again, and talked with them. And he took Simeon from them and bound
        him before their eyes.
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Then Joseph gave a command to fill their sacks with grain, to restore
        every man\u2019s money to his sack, and to give them provisions for the journey.
        Thus he did for them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'So they loaded their donkeys with the grain and departed from there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'But as one of  them opened his sack to give his donkey feed at the
        encampment, he saw his money; and there it was, in the mouth of his sack. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "So he said to his brothers, \u201CMy money has been restored, and
        there it is, in my sack!\u201D Then their hearts failed them and they were
        afraid, saying to one another, \u201CWhat is this that God has done to us?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Then they went to Jacob their father in the land of Canaan and told
        him all that had happened to them, saying: '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "\u201CThe man who  is lord of the land spoke roughly to us, and took
        us for spies of the country. "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "But we said to him, \u2018We are honest men; we are not spies. "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "We are twelve brothers, sons of our father; one is no more, and the
        youngest is with our father this day in the land of Canaan.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "Then the man, the lord of the country, said to us, \u2018By this
        I will know that you are honest men: Leave one of your brothers here with
        me, take food  for the famine of your households, and be gone. "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "And bring your youngest brother to me; so I shall know that you are
        not spies, but that you are honest men. I will grant your brother to you,
        and you may trade in the land.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "Then it happened as they emptied their sacks, that surprisingly each
        man\u2019s bundle of money was in his sack; and when they and their father
        saw the bundles of money, they were afraid. "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "And Jacob their father said to them, \u201CYou have bereaved me:
        Joseph is no more, Simeon is no more, and you want to take Benjamin. All
        these things are against me.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "Then Reuben spoke to his father, saying, \u201CKill my two sons if
        I do not bring him back to you; put him in my hands, and I will bring him
        back to you.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "But he said, \u201CMy son shall not go down with you, for his brother
        is dead, and he is left alone. If any calamity should befall him along the
        way in which you go, then you would bring down my gray hair with sorrow to
        the grave.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Joseph\u2019s Brothers Return with Benjamin"
      title: "Joseph\u2019s Brothers Return with Benjamin"
      number: 1
      content: 'Now the famine was  severe in the land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And it came to pass, when they had eaten up the grain which they
        had brought from Egypt, that their father said to them, \u201CGo back, buy
        us a little food.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "But Judah spoke to him, saying, \u201CThe man solemnly warned us,
        saying, \u2018You shall not see my face unless your brother is with you.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'If you send our brother with us, we will go down and buy you food. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "But if you will not send him, we will not go down; for the man said
        to us, \u2018You shall not see my face unless your brother is with you.\u2019
        \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And Israel said, \u201CWhy did you deal so wrongfully with me as
        to tell the man whether you had still another brother?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "But they said, \u201CThe man asked us pointedly about ourselves and
        our family, saying, \u2018Is your father still alive? Have you another brother?\u2019
        And we told him according to these words. Could we possibly have known that
        he would say, \u2018Bring your brother down\u2019?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then Judah said to Israel his father, \u201CSend the lad with me,
        and we will arise and go, that we may live and not die, both we and you and
        also our little ones. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'I myself will be surety for him; from my hand you shall require him.
        If I do not bring him back to you and set him before you, then let me bear
        the blame forever. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "For if we had not lingered, surely by now we would have returned
        this second time.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And their father Israel said to them, \u201CIf it  must  be so, then
        do this: Take some of the best fruits of the land in your vessels and carry
        down a present for the man\u2014a little balm and a little honey, spices
        and myrrh, pistachio nuts and almonds. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Take double money in your hand, and take back in your hand the money
        that was returned in the mouth of your sacks; perhaps it was an oversight. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Take your brother also, and arise, go back to the man. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And may God Almighty give you mercy before the man, that he may release
        your other brother and Benjamin. If I am bereaved, I am bereaved!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'So the men took that present and Benjamin, and they took double money
        in their hand, and arose and went down to Egypt; and they stood before Joseph. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "When Joseph saw Benjamin with them, he said to the steward of his
        house, \u201CTake these men to my home, and slaughter an animal and make
        ready; for these men will dine with me at noon.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Then the man did as Joseph ordered, and the man brought the men into
        Joseph\u2019s house."
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Now the men were afraid because they were brought into Joseph\u2019s
        house; and they said, \u201CIt  is because of the money, which was returned
        in our sacks the first time, that we are brought in, so that he may make
        a case against us and seize us, to take us as slaves with our donkeys.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "When they drew near to the steward of Joseph\u2019s house, they talked
        with him at the door of the house, "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "and said, \u201CO sir, we indeed came down the first time to buy
        food; "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "but it happened, when we came to the encampment, that we opened our
        sacks, and there, each man\u2019s money was in the mouth of his sack, our
        money in full weight; so we have brought it back in our hand. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "And we have brought down other money in our hands to buy food. We
        do not know who put our money in our sacks.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "But he said, \u201CPeace be with you, do not be afraid. Your God
        and the God of your father has given you treasure in your sacks; I had your
        money.\u201D Then he brought Simeon out to them."
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "So the man brought the men into Joseph\u2019s house and gave them
        water, and they washed their feet; and he gave their donkeys feed. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Then they made the present ready for Joseph\u2019s coming at noon,
        for they heard that they would eat bread there."
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'And when Joseph came home, they brought him the present which was
        in their hand into the house, and bowed down before him to the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Then he asked them about their well-being, and said, \u201CIs your
        father well, the old man of whom you spoke? Is he still alive?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "And they answered, \u201CYour servant our father is in good health;
        he is still alive.\u201D And they bowed their heads down and prostrated themselves."
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Then he lifted his eyes and saw his brother Benjamin, his mother\u2019s
        son, and said, \u201CIs this your younger brother of whom you spoke to me?\u201D
        And he said, \u201CGod be gracious to you, my son.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Now his heart yearned for his brother; so Joseph made haste and sought
        somewhere to weep. And he went into his chamber and wept there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Then he washed his face and came out; and he restrained himself,
        and said, \u201CServe the bread.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'So they set him a place by himself, and them by themselves, and the
        Egyptians who ate with him by themselves; because the Egyptians could not
        eat food with the Hebrews, for that is  an abomination to the Egyptians. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'And they sat before him, the firstborn according to his birthright
        and the youngest according to his youth; and the men looked in astonishment
        at one another. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "Then he took servings to them from before him, but Benjamin\u2019s
        serving was five times as much as any of theirs. So they drank and were merry
        with him."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Joseph\u2019s Cup"
      title: "Joseph\u2019s Cup"
      number: 1
      content: "And he commanded the steward of his house, saying, \u201CFill the
        men\u2019s sacks with food, as much as they can carry, and put each man\u2019s
        money in the mouth of his sack. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Also put my cup, the silver cup, in the mouth of the sack of the
        youngest, and his grain money.\u201D So he did according to the word that
        Joseph had spoken. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'As soon as the morning dawned, the men were sent away, they and their
        donkeys. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "When they had gone out of the city, and were not yet far off, Joseph
        said to his steward, \u201CGet up, follow the men; and when you overtake
        them, say to them, \u2018Why have you repaid evil for good? "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Is not this the  one from which my lord drinks, and with which he
        indeed practices divination? You have done evil in so doing.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'So he overtook them, and he spoke to them these same words. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And they said to him, \u201CWhy does my lord say these words? Far
        be it from us that your servants should do such a thing. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Look, we brought back to you from the land of Canaan the money which
        we found in the mouth of our sacks. How then could we steal silver or gold
        from your lord\u2019s house? "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "With whomever of your servants it is found, let him die, and we also
        will be my lord\u2019s slaves.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And he said, \u201CNow also let it be according to your words; he
        with whom it is found shall be my slave, and you shall be blameless.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Then each man speedily let down his sack to the ground, and each
        opened his sack. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "So he searched. He began with the oldest and left off with the youngest;
        and the cup was found in Benjamin\u2019s sack. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: Then they tore their clothes, and each man loaded his donkey and returned
        to the city.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "So Judah and his brothers came to Joseph\u2019s house, and he was
        still there; and they fell before him on the ground. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And Joseph said to them, \u201CWhat deed is this you have done? Did
        you not know that such a man as I can certainly practice divination?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Then Judah said, \u201CWhat shall we say to my lord? What shall we
        speak? Or how shall we clear ourselves? God has found out the iniquity of
        your servants; here we are, my lord\u2019s slaves, both we and he also with
        whom the cup was found.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '17: Judah Intercedes for Benjamin'
      title: Judah Intercedes for Benjamin
      number: 17
      content: "But he said, \u201CFar be it from me that I should do so; the man
        in whose hand the cup was found, he shall be my slave. And as for you, go
        up in peace to your father.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Then Judah came near to him and said: \u201CO my lord, please let
        your servant speak a word in my lord\u2019s hearing, and do not let your
        anger burn against your servant; for you are even like Pharaoh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "My lord asked his servants, saying, \u2018Have you a father or a
        brother?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And we said to my lord, \u2018We have a father, an old man, and a
        child of his old age, who  is young; his brother is dead, and he alone is
        left of his mother\u2019s children, and his father loves him.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Then you said to your servants, \u2018Bring him down to me, that
        I may set my eyes on him.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "And we said to my lord, \u2018The lad cannot leave his father, for
        if he should leave his father, his  father would die.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "But you said to your servants, \u2018Unless your youngest brother
        comes down with you, you shall see my face no more.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "\u201CSo it was, when we went up to your servant my father, that
        we told him the words of my lord. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "And our father said, \u2018Go back and buy us a little food.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "But we said, \u2018We cannot go down; if our youngest brother is
        with us, then we will go down; for we may not see the man\u2019s face unless
        our youngest brother is with us.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Then your servant my father said to us, \u2018You know that my wife
        bore me two sons; "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "and the one went out from me, and I said, \u201CSurely he is torn
        to pieces\u201D; and I have not seen him since. "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "But if you take this one also from me, and calamity befalls him,
        you shall bring down my gray hair with sorrow to the grave.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "\u201CNow therefore, when I come to your servant my father, and the
        lad is not with us, since his life is bound up in the lad\u2019s life, "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'it will happen, when he sees that the lad is not with  us, that he
        will die. So your servants will bring down the gray hair of your servant
        our father with sorrow to the grave. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "For your servant became surety for the lad to my father, saying,
        \u2018If I do not bring him back to you, then I shall bear the blame before
        my father forever.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'Now therefore, please let your servant remain instead of the lad
        as a slave to my lord, and let the lad go up with his brothers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "For how shall I go up to my father if the lad is not with me, lest
        perhaps I see the evil that would come upon my father?\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Joseph Revealed to His Brothers'
      title: Joseph Revealed to His Brothers
      number: 1
      content: "Then Joseph could not restrain himself before all those who stood
        by him, and he cried out, \u201CMake everyone go out from me!\u201D So no
        one stood with him while Joseph made himself known to his brothers. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: And he wept aloud, and the Egyptians and the house of Pharaoh heard
        it.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then Joseph said to his brothers, \u201CI am Joseph; does my father
        still live?\u201D But his brothers could not answer him, for they were dismayed
        in his presence. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And Joseph said to his brothers, \u201CPlease come near to me.\u201D
        So they came near. Then he said: \u201CI am Joseph your brother, whom you
        sold into Egypt. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'But now, do not therefore be grieved or angry with yourselves because
        you sold me here; for God sent me before you to preserve life. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'For these two years the famine has  been in the land, and there 
        are still five years in which there  will  be neither plowing nor harvesting. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And God sent me before you to preserve a posterity for you in the
        earth, and to save your lives by a great deliverance. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: So now it  was not you who sent me here, but God; and He has made
        me a father to Pharaoh, and lord of all his house, and a ruler throughout
        all the land of Egypt.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CHurry and go up to my father, and say to him, \u2018Thus says
        your son Joseph: \u201CGod has made me lord of all Egypt; come down to me,
        do not tarry. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "You shall dwell in the land of Goshen, and you shall be near to me,
        you and your children, your children\u2019s children, your flocks and your
        herds, and all that you have. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "There I will provide for you, lest you and your household, and all
        that you have, come to poverty; for there  are still five years of famine.\u201D
        \u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CAnd behold, your eyes and the eyes of my brother Benjamin see
        that it  is  my mouth that speaks to you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "So you shall tell my father of all my glory in Egypt, and of all
        that you have seen; and you shall hurry and bring my father down here.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then he fell on his brother Benjamin\u2019s neck and wept, and Benjamin
        wept on his neck. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: Moreover he kissed all his brothers and wept over them, and after
        that his brothers talked with him.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Now the report of it was heard in Pharaoh\u2019s house, saying, \u201CJoseph\u2019s
        brothers have come.\u201D So it pleased Pharaoh and his servants well. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And Pharaoh said to Joseph, \u201CSay to your brothers, \u2018Do
        this: Load your animals and depart; go to the land of Canaan. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Bring your father and your households and come to me; I will give
        you the best of the land of Egypt, and you will eat the fat of the land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Now you are commanded\u2014do this: Take carts out of the land of
        Egypt for your little ones and your wives; bring your father and come. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Also do not be concerned about your goods, for the best of all the
        land of Egypt is yours.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Then the sons of Israel did so; and Joseph gave them carts, according
        to the command of Pharaoh, and he gave them provisions for the journey. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'He gave to all of them, to each man, changes of garments; but to
        Benjamin he gave three hundred pieces of silver and five changes of garments. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And he sent to his father these things: ten donkeys loaded with the
        good things of Egypt, and ten female donkeys loaded with grain, bread, and
        food for his father for the journey. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "So he sent his brothers away, and they departed; and he said to them,
        \u201CSee that you do not become troubled along the way.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Then they went up out of Egypt, and came to the land of Canaan to
        Jacob their father. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "And they told him, saying, \u201CJoseph is still alive, and he is
        governor over all the land of Egypt.\u201D And Jacob\u2019s heart stood still,
        because he did not believe them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'But when they told him all the words which Joseph had said to them,
        and when he saw the carts which Joseph had sent to carry him, the spirit
        of Jacob their father revived. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Then Israel said, \u201CIt  is enough. Joseph my son is still alive.
        I will go and see him before I die.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Jacob\u2019s Journey to Egypt"
      title: "Jacob\u2019s Journey to Egypt"
      number: 1
      content: 'So Israel took his journey with all that he had, and came to Beersheba,
        and offered sacrifices to the God of his father Isaac. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Then God spoke to Israel in the visions of the night, and said, \u201CJacob,
        Jacob!\u201DAnd he said, \u201CHere I am.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "So He said, \u201CI am God, the God of your father; do not fear to
        go down to Egypt, for I will make of you a great nation there. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "I will go down with you to Egypt, and I will also surely bring you
        up again; and Joseph will put his hand on your eyes.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Then Jacob arose from Beersheba; and the sons of Israel carried their
        father Jacob, their little ones, and their wives, in the carts which Pharaoh
        had sent to carry him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'So they took their livestock and their goods, which they had acquired
        in the land of Canaan, and went to Egypt, Jacob and all his descendants with
        him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "His sons and his sons\u2019 sons, his daughters and his sons\u2019
        daughters, and all his descendants he brought with him to Egypt."
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Now these were the names of the children of Israel, Jacob and his
        sons, who went to Egypt: Reuben was Jacob\u2019s firstborn. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'The sons of Reuben were Hanoch, Pallu, Hezron, and Carmi. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'The sons of Simeon were Jemuel, Jamin, Ohad, Jachin, Zohar, and Shaul,
        the son of a Canaanite woman. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'The sons of Levi were Gershon, Kohath, and Merari. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'The sons of Judah were  Er, Onan, Shelah, Perez, and Zerah (but Er
        and Onan died in the land of Canaan). The sons of Perez were Hezron and Hamul. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'The sons of Issachar were Tola, Puvah, Job, and Shimron. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'The sons of Zebulun were Sered, Elon, and Jahleel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: These were the sons of Leah, whom she bore to Jacob in Padan Aram,
        with his daughter Dinah. All the persons, his sons and his daughters, were
        thirty-three.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'The sons of Gad were Ziphion, Haggi, Shuni, Ezbon, Eri, Arodi, and
        Areli. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'The sons of Asher were Jimnah, Ishuah, Isui, Beriah, and Serah, their
        sister. And the sons of Beriah were Heber and Malchiel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'These were the sons of Zilpah, whom Laban gave to Leah his daughter;
        and these she bore to Jacob: sixteen persons.'
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "The sons of Rachel, Jacob\u2019s wife, were Joseph and Benjamin. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And to Joseph in the land of Egypt were born Manasseh and Ephraim,
        whom Asenath, the daughter of Poti-Pherah priest of On, bore to him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'The sons of Benjamin were Belah, Becher, Ashbel, Gera, Naaman, Ehi,
        Rosh, Muppim, Huppim, and Ard. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'These were the sons of Rachel, who were born to Jacob: fourteen persons
        in all.'
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'The son of Dan was Hushim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'The sons of Naphtali were Jahzeel, Guni, Jezer, and Shillem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'These were the sons of Bilhah, whom Laban gave to Rachel his daughter,
        and she bore these to Jacob: seven persons in all.'
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "All the persons who went with Jacob to Egypt, who came from his body,
        besides Jacob\u2019s sons\u2019 wives, were sixty-six persons in all. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: Jacob Settles in Goshen'
      title: Jacob Settles in Goshen
      number: 27
      content: And the sons of Joseph who were born to him in Egypt were two persons.
        All the persons of the house of Jacob who went to Egypt were seventy.
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Then he sent Judah before him to Joseph, to point out before him
        the  way to Goshen. And they came to the land of Goshen. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: So Joseph made ready his chariot and went up to Goshen to meet his
        father Israel; and he presented himself to him, and fell on his neck and
        wept on his neck a good while.
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "And Israel said to Joseph, \u201CNow let me die, since I have seen
        your face, because you are still alive.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Then Joseph said to his brothers and to his father\u2019s household,
        \u201CI will go up and tell Pharaoh, and say to him, \u2018My brothers and
        those of my father\u2019s house, who were in the land of Canaan, have come
        to me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "And the men are  shepherds, for their occupation has been to feed
        livestock; and they have brought their flocks, their herds, and all that
        they have.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "So it shall be, when Pharaoh calls you and says, \u2018What is your
        occupation?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "that you shall say, \u2018Your servants\u2019 occupation has been
        with livestock from our youth even till now, both we and also our fathers,\u2019
        that you may dwell in the land of Goshen; for every shepherd is  an abomination
        to the Egyptians.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: "Then Joseph went and told Pharaoh, and said, \u201CMy father and
        my brothers, their flocks and their herds and all that they possess, have
        come from the land of Canaan; and indeed they are in the land of Goshen.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And he took five men from among his brothers and presented them to
        Pharaoh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then Pharaoh said to his brothers, \u201CWhat is your occupation?\u201DAnd
        they said to Pharaoh, \u201CYour servants are shepherds, both we and also
        our fathers.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And they said to Pharaoh, \u201CWe have come to dwell in the land,
        because your servants have no pasture for their flocks, for the famine is
        severe in the land of Canaan. Now therefore, please let your servants dwell
        in the land of Goshen.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then Pharaoh spoke to Joseph, saying, \u201CYour father and your
        brothers have come to you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "The land of Egypt is before you. Have your father and brothers dwell
        in the best of the land; let them dwell in the land of Goshen. And if you
        know any competent men among them, then make them chief herdsmen over my
        livestock.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Then Joseph brought in his father Jacob and set him before Pharaoh;
        and Jacob blessed Pharaoh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Pharaoh said to Jacob, \u201CHow old are you?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And Jacob said to Pharaoh, \u201CThe days of the years of my pilgrimage
        are  one hundred and thirty years; few and evil have been the days of the
        years of my life, and they have not attained to the days of the years of
        the life of my fathers in the days of their pilgrimage.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: So Jacob blessed Pharaoh, and went out from before Pharaoh.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And Joseph situated his father and his brothers, and gave them a
        possession in the land of Egypt, in the best of the land, in the land of
        Rameses, as Pharaoh had commanded. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: Joseph Deals with the Famine'
      title: Joseph Deals with the Famine
      number: 12
      content: "Then Joseph provided his father, his brothers, and all his father\u2019s
        household with bread, according to the number in their families."
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Now there  was no bread in all the land; for the famine was very
        severe, so that the land of Egypt and the land of Canaan languished because
        of the famine. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And Joseph gathered up all the money that was found in the land of
        Egypt and in the land of Canaan, for the grain which they bought; and Joseph
        brought the money into Pharaoh\u2019s house."
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "So when the money failed in the land of Egypt and in the land of
        Canaan, all the Egyptians came to Joseph and said, \u201CGive us bread, for
        why should we die in your presence? For the money has failed.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Then Joseph said, \u201CGive your livestock, and I will give you
        bread for your livestock, if the money is gone.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: So they brought their livestock to Joseph, and Joseph gave them bread
        in  exchange for the horses, the flocks, the cattle of the herds, and for
        the donkeys. Thus he fed them with bread in  exchange for all their livestock
        that year.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "When that year had ended, they came to him the next year and said
        to him, \u201CWe will not hide from my lord that our money is gone; my lord
        also has our herds of livestock. There is nothing left in the sight of my
        lord but our bodies and our lands. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Why should we die before your eyes, both we and our land? Buy us
        and our land for bread, and we and our land will be servants of Pharaoh;
        give us seed, that we may live and not die, that the land may not be desolate.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Then Joseph bought all the land of Egypt for Pharaoh; for every man
        of the Egyptians sold his field, because the famine was severe upon them.
        So the land became Pharaoh\u2019s. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And as for the people, he moved them into the cities, from one end
        of the borders of Egypt to the other end. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: Only the land of the priests he did not buy; for the priests had rations
        allotted  to  them by Pharaoh, and they ate their rations which Pharaoh gave
        them; therefore they did not sell their lands.
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Then Joseph said to the people, \u201CIndeed I have bought you and
        your land this day for Pharaoh. Look, here  is seed for you, and you shall
        sow the land. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "And it shall come to pass in the harvest that you shall give one-fifth
        to Pharaoh. Four-fifths shall be your own, as seed for the field and for
        your food, for those of your households and as food for your little ones.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "So they said, \u201CYou have saved our lives; let us find favor in
        the sight of my lord, and we will be Pharaoh\u2019s servants.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: "26: Joseph\u2019s Vow to Jacob"
      title: "Joseph\u2019s Vow to Jacob"
      number: 26
      content: "And Joseph made it a law over the land of Egypt to this day, that
        Pharaoh should have one-fifth, except for the land of the priests only, which
        did not become Pharaoh\u2019s."
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'So Israel dwelt in the land of Egypt, in the country of Goshen; and
        they had possessions there and grew and multiplied exceedingly. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "And Jacob lived in the land of Egypt seventeen years. So the length
        of Jacob\u2019s life was one hundred and forty-seven years. "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "When the time drew near that Israel must die, he called his son Joseph
        and said to him, \u201CNow if I have found favor in your sight, please put
        your hand under my thigh, and deal kindly and truly with me. Please do not
        bury me in Egypt, "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "but let me lie with my fathers; you shall carry me out of Egypt and
        bury me in their burial place.\u201DAnd he said, \u201CI will do as you have
        said.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Then he said, \u201CSwear to me.\u201D And he swore to him. So Israel
        bowed himself on the head of the bed."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Jacob Blesses Joseph\u2019s Sons"
      title: "Jacob Blesses Joseph\u2019s Sons"
      number: 1
      content: "Now it came to pass after these things that Joseph was told, \u201CIndeed
        your father is sick\u201D; and he took with him his two sons, Manasseh and
        Ephraim. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And Jacob was told, \u201CLook, your son Joseph is coming to you\u201D;
        and Israel strengthened himself and sat up on the bed. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then Jacob said to Joseph: \u201CGod Almighty appeared to me at Luz
        in the land of Canaan and blessed me, "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "and said to me, \u2018Behold, I will make you fruitful and multiply
        you, and I will make of you a multitude of people, and give this land to
        your descendants after you as an everlasting possession.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And now your two sons, Ephraim and Manasseh, who were born to you
        in the land of Egypt before I came to you in Egypt, are mine; as Reuben and
        Simeon, they shall be mine. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Your offspring whom you beget after them shall be yours; they will
        be called by the name of their brothers in their inheritance. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "But as for me, when I came from Padan, Rachel died beside me in the
        land of Canaan on the way, when there  was but a little distance to go to
        Ephrath; and I buried her there on the way to Ephrath (that is, Bethlehem).\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then Israel saw Joseph\u2019s sons, and said, \u201CWho are these?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And Joseph said to his father, \u201CThey are my sons, whom God has
        given me in this place.\u201DAnd he said, \u201CPlease bring them to me,
        and I will bless them.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Now the eyes of Israel were dim with age, so  that he could not see.
        Then Joseph brought them near him, and he kissed them and embraced them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And Israel said to Joseph, \u201CI had not thought to see your face;
        but in fact, God has also shown me your offspring!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'So Joseph brought them from beside his knees, and he bowed down with
        his face to the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And Joseph took them both, Ephraim with his right hand toward Israel\u2019s
        left hand, and Manasseh with his left hand toward Israel\u2019s right hand,
        and brought them near him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then Israel stretched out his right hand and laid it on Ephraim\u2019s
        head, who was the younger, and his left hand on Manasseh\u2019s head, guiding
        his hands knowingly, for Manasseh was the firstborn. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And he blessed Joseph, and said:\u201CGod, before whom my fathers
        Abraham and Isaac walked,The God who has fed me all my life long to this
        day,"
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "The Angel who has redeemed me from all evil,Bless the lads;Let my
        name be named upon them,And the name of my fathers Abraham and Isaac;And
        let them grow into a multitude in the midst of the earth.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Now when Joseph saw that his father laid his right hand on the head
        of Ephraim, it displeased him; so he took hold of his father\u2019s hand
        to remove it from Ephraim\u2019s head to Manasseh\u2019s head. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And Joseph said to his father, \u201CNot so, my father, for this
        one  is the firstborn; put your right hand on his head.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "But his father refused and said, \u201CI know, my son, I know. He
        also shall become a people, and he also shall be great; but truly his younger
        brother shall be greater than he, and his descendants shall become a multitude
        of nations.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "So he blessed them that day, saying, \u201CBy you Israel will bless,
        saying, \u2018May God make you as Ephraim and as Manasseh!\u2019 \u201D And
        thus he set Ephraim before Manasseh."
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Then Israel said to Joseph, \u201CBehold, I am dying, but God will
        be with you and bring you back to the land of your fathers. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Moreover I have given to you one portion above your brothers, which
        I took from the hand of the Amorite with my sword and my bow.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Jacob\u2019s Last Words to His Sons"
      title: "Jacob\u2019s Last Words to His Sons"
      number: 1
      content: "And Jacob called his sons and said, \u201CGather together, that I
        may tell you what shall befall you in the last days:"
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CGather together and hear, you sons of Jacob,And listen to Israel
        your father."
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CReuben, you are my firstborn,My might and the beginning of
        my strength,The excellency of dignity and the excellency of power."
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Unstable as water, you shall not excel,Because you went up to your
        father\u2019s bed;Then you defiled it\u2014He went up to my couch."
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CSimeon and Levi are brothers;Instruments of cruelty are  in
        their dwelling place."
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: Let not my soul enter their council;Let not my honor be united to
        their assembly;For in their anger they slew a man,And in their self-will
        they hamstrung an ox.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: Cursed be their anger, for it  is fierce;And their wrath, for it is
        cruel!I will divide them in JacobAnd scatter them in Israel.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CJudah, you are  he whom your brothers shall praise;Your hand
        shall  be on the neck of your enemies;Your father\u2019s children shall bow
        down before you."
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Judah is  a lion\u2019s whelp;From the prey, my son, you have gone
        up.He bows down, he lies down as a lion;And as a lion, who shall rouse him?"
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: The scepter shall not depart from Judah,Nor a lawgiver from between
        his feet,Until Shiloh comes;And to Him shall  be the obedience of the people.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Binding his donkey to the vine,And his donkey\u2019s colt to the
        choice vine,He washed his garments in wine,And his clothes in the blood of
        grapes."
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: His eyes are darker than wine,And his teeth whiter than milk.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CZebulun shall dwell by the haven of the sea;He shall  become
        a haven for ships,And his border shall adjoin Sidon."
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CIssachar is a strong donkey,Lying down between two burdens;"
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: He saw that rest was good,And that the land was pleasant;He bowed
        his shoulder to bear a  burden,And became a band of slaves.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CDan shall judge his peopleAs one of the tribes of Israel."
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Dan shall be a serpent by the way,A viper by the path,That bites
        the horse\u2019s heelsSo that its rider shall fall backward."
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: I have waited for your salvation, O Lord!
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CGad, a troop shall tramp upon him,But he shall triumph at last."
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CBread from Asher shall  be rich,And he shall yield royal dainties."
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CNaphtali  is a deer let loose;He uses beautiful words."
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u201CJoseph is a fruitful bough,A fruitful bough by a well;His branches
        run over the wall."
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: The archers have bitterly grieved him,Shot at  him and hated him.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: But his bow remained in strength,And the arms of his hands were made
        strongBy the hands of the Mighty God of Jacob(From there is the Shepherd,
        the Stone of Israel),
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: By the God of your father who will help you,And by the Almighty who
        will bless youWith blessings of heaven above,Blessings of the deep that lies
        beneath,Blessings of the breasts and of the womb.
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: The blessings of your fatherHave excelled the blessings of my ancestors,Up
        to the utmost bound of the everlasting hills.They shall be on the head of
        Joseph,And on the crown of the head of him who was separate from his brothers.
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "\u201CBenjamin is a ravenous wolf;In the morning he shall devour
        the prey,And at night he shall divide the spoil.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: "28: Jacob\u2019s Death and Burial"
      title: "Jacob\u2019s Death and Burial"
      number: 28
      content: All these are the twelve tribes of Israel, and this is what their
        father spoke to them. And he blessed them; he blessed each one according
        to his own blessing.
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Then he charged them and said to them: \u201CI am to be gathered
        to my people; bury me with my fathers in the cave that is in the field of
        Ephron the Hittite, "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'in the cave that is in the field of Machpelah, which is before Mamre
        in the land of Canaan, which Abraham bought with the field of Ephron the
        Hittite as a possession for a burial place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'There they buried Abraham and Sarah his wife, there they buried Isaac
        and Rebekah his wife, and there I buried Leah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "The field and the cave that is there were purchased from the sons
        of Heth.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: And when Jacob had finished commanding his sons, he drew his feet
        up into the bed and breathed his last, and was gathered to his people.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: "Then Joseph fell on his father\u2019s face, and wept over him, and
        kissed him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And Joseph commanded his servants the physicians to embalm his father.
        So the physicians embalmed Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: Forty days were required for him, for such are the days required for
        those who are embalmed; and the Egyptians mourned for him seventy days.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Now when the days of his mourning were past, Joseph spoke to the
        household of Pharaoh, saying, \u201CIf now I have found favor in your eyes,
        please speak in the hearing of Pharaoh, saying, "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u2018My father made me swear, saying, \u201CBehold, I am dying;
        in my grave which I dug for myself in the land of Canaan, there you shall
        bury me.\u201D Now therefore, please let me go up and bury my father, and
        I will come back.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And Pharaoh said, \u201CGo up and bury your father, as he made you
        swear.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'So Joseph went up to bury his father; and with him went up all the
        servants of Pharaoh, the elders of his house, and all the elders of the land
        of Egypt, '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "as well as all the house of Joseph, his brothers, and his father\u2019s
        house. Only their little ones, their flocks, and their herds they left in
        the land of Goshen. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: And there went up with him both chariots and horsemen, and it was
        a very great gathering.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Then they came to the threshing floor of Atad, which is beyond the
        Jordan, and they mourned there with a great and very solemn lamentation.
        He observed seven days of mourning for his father. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And when the inhabitants of the land, the Canaanites, saw the mourning
        at the threshing floor of Atad, they said, \u201CThis is a deep mourning
        of the Egyptians.\u201D Therefore its name was called Abel Mizraim, which
        is beyond the Jordan."
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'So his sons did for him just as he had commanded them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'For his sons carried him to the land of Canaan, and buried him in
        the cave of the field of Machpelah, before Mamre, which Abraham bought with
        the field from Ephron the Hittite as property for a burial place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: Joseph Reassures His Brothers'
      title: Joseph Reassures His Brothers
      number: 14
      content: And after he had buried his father, Joseph returned to Egypt, he and
        his brothers and all who went up with him to bury his father.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "When Joseph\u2019s brothers saw that their father was dead, they
        said, \u201CPerhaps Joseph will hate us, and may actually repay us for all
        the evil which we did to him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "So they sent messengers to Joseph, saying, \u201CBefore your father
        died he commanded, saying, "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u2018Thus you shall say to Joseph: \u201CI beg you, please forgive
        the trespass of your brothers and their sin; for they did evil to you.\u201D
        \u2019 Now, please, forgive the trespass of the servants of the God of your
        father.\u201D And Joseph wept when they spoke to him."
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Then his brothers also went and fell down before his face, and they
        said, \u201CBehold, we are your servants.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Joseph said to them, \u201CDo not be afraid, for am I in the place
        of God? "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'But as for you, you meant evil against me; but  God meant it for
        good, in order to bring it about as it  is this day, to save many people
        alive. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: Death of Joseph'
      title: Death of Joseph
      number: 21
      content: "Now therefore, do not be afraid; I will provide for you and your
        little ones.\u201D And he comforted them and spoke kindly to them."
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "So Joseph dwelt in Egypt, he and his father\u2019s household. And
        Joseph lived one hundred and ten years. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Joseph saw Ephraim\u2019s children to the third generation.  The
        children of Machir, the son of Manasseh, were also brought up on Joseph\u2019s
        knees."
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "And Joseph said to his brethren, \u201CI am dying; but God will surely
        visit you, and bring you out of this land to the land of which He swore to
        Abraham, to Isaac, and to Jacob.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Then Joseph took an oath from the children of Israel, saying, \u201CGod
        will surely visit you, and you shall carry up my bones from here.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: So Joseph died, being one hundred and ten years old; and they embalmed
        him, and he was put in a coffin in Egypt.
      comments: []
